column10:
Hey there—it’s Dickie.

Do you ever feel like no matter how hard you try, you just can’t
get anywhere?

You’re toiling away, day after day, trying to figure out how to
create the “perfect” side hustle to plan your escape from your 9
to 5 (which is slowly crushing you)…

I get it, we hear this all the time from the people who are just
about to jump inside our Premium Ghostwriting Academy (PGA).

But it’s not their (or your) fault. The internet bombards you
with 100 different plans, strategies, frameworks—quick hacks to
get you instant results which (surprise, surprise), never
materialize.

The truth is, there are 3 (brutal) reasons why you’re going
nowhere.

Let’s break them down—and exactly how to fix them:

*********************************************
Reason #1: You haven’t committed to anything.
*********************************************

You need to pick SOMETHING.

Stop trying to figure out whether:

* Investing in crypto
* Starting a dropshipping business
* Or going all-in on Premium Ghostwriting…

…is the “thing” for you.

Instead, pick one and fully COMMIT.

Because it’s not the actual project or result that matters—it’s
the skills you build and the person you become by working on it
that matters the most.

**********************************************
Reason #2: You don’t have any way to practice.
**********************************************

What happens when you don’t commit?

You have no way of practicing the skills you need to master to
move the needle forward in your business or your side hustle.

Instead of focusing on:

* Doing another hour of copywork
* Reading more books on how to start a side hustle
* Listening to another podcast on how to master the art of sales

Pick one of those skills and take ACTION toward mastering it.

​
This leads us to our final point.

**************************************************
Reason #3: You’re trying to do things on your own.
**************************************************

Why waste hundreds (if not thousands) of hours trying to figure
out everything for yourself?

Instead, find the person (or people) who know how to get to where
you want to be and learn everything you can from them. The speed
at which you acquire the skills and the confidence you need will
far outweigh the cost it takes to work with them.

People tell us all the time they can figure out everything on
their own (like how to delight clients, run a business,
ghostwrite something they’ve never written before, etc.).

But here’s a question we got today inside PGA:

​
How would you handle this situation?

Luckily, with PGA, you have a dedicated 1:1 Success Coach to ask
and weekly sales clinics to go in depth on situations like these.
And this is just one of MANY questions we get inside the
community.

So, would you rather invest in yourself now or fritter away the
only resource you CAN’T renew—time?

I know which one I’d choose.

​

----------------------------------------
So, are you ready to take the next step?
----------------------------------------

-----------------------------------------------------------------
​Click here to stop making excuses and kickstart your
ghostwriting side hustle. (

)​
-----------------------------------------------------------------

I can’t wait to see you on the inside to help you crush the rest
of 2024 and into 2025!

—Dickie

Co-founder, Premium Ghostwriting Academy.

PS… Want to see what it looks like when you stop trying to do
things on your own?

Here’s Thomas, one of our most successful students inside PGA. He
worked with one of our all-star enrollment advisors Connor to get

And then took the plunge and joined us inside PGA to take his
business to the next level (and hasn’t looked back since).

column7: Are you *really* in control of your income?
column9:
Here’s a question for you:

If you worked twice as hard (or you learned twice as fast), would
your income double?

Take a second to think about that—but please be brutally honest
with yourself.

…

..

.

If the answer is “yes,” then you’re probably working on the right
opportunity—that’s awesome. You can go ahead and archive this
email.

But if it’s “no,” then you might be on the wrong career path.

Because that means you don’t really have control over your
earning potential (or your time).

And that’s OK.

I was in this camp, too, before I quit my job on Wall Street 4
years ago.

However, once you confront this truth, you have 2 options:

* You can continue to do nothing about it—and let others decide
how much money you make each year, how long you have to work, and
from where.
​
* OR you can start executing a plan to change your trajectory—so
you can put yourself in a position where YOU are in control of
your time and your income.

Now, if option #2 resonates more with you, then I think you might
find this podcast I just did with my friend Darren Lee helpful. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/p9uz255lqzi9h3e8x6nuqhp34x033hr/3ohphdu7ermw0ktp/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj1wNzNQMEwta2hoMA==
)​

We talked about my journey and how I was able to go from trying
to save $1,000/mo (so I could hopefully retire by the time I was
65) to:

* Making my first $5,000 on the Internet
* Getting full control over my time and my income
* And building a series of businesses en route to making
$10M/year

​Here’s the link again so you can check it out. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/p9uz255lqzi9h3e8x6nuqhp34x033hr/3ohphdu7ermw0ktp/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj1wNzNQMEwta2hoMA==

And if you do end up giving it a watch, hit reply and let me know
if it was helpful!

Talk soon,

Dickie

column7: Father of 2 discovers new family-flexible career
column9:
Happy Father’s Day, Candace.

 

Today, I want to “hand the mic over” to my friend and mentor at my Certification School - Viraj Oza.

Who recorded this deeply inspiring video that every parent needs to see:

Video thumbnail ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/mentor-coaching-11/?el=mentor-video-viraj-email-172-7&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+172-7&utm_content_name=Father+of+2+discovers+new+family-flexible+career&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )
7 years ago, Viraj was working a high-flying corporate career.

 

Commuting 4 hours to the office and back…

 

Then coming home drained, burnt out, and with very little energy for his young family.

 

He hated how things were.

 

But he didn’t feel he could stop.

 

So he just kept going…

 

and going…

 

and going…

 

Till one day his health said “No more” and pulled the brakes.

 

That hard stop gave him the time to really refocus his priorities.

 

He realized he couldn’t go back to his corporate career.

 

He didn’t want to be a part-time dad anymore.

 

He wanted to be there every morning to take his kids to school.

 

And finish work at 3pm to pick them up and spend the evening with them.

 

To be present at home, 100%.

Becoming a coach gave him that freedom over his time.

 

And more than that…

 

It gave him tools and communication skills that have helped him be a happier, more connected, and more present father at home.

 

He used what he learned about coaching with his own children…

 

And now they’re bigger, he’s seeing them use those exact same techniques to deal with stress or arguments at home too.

 

If you want to hear Viraj’s inspiring full story:

 

Click here and watch Viraj’s Father’s Day video → ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/mentor-coaching-11/?el=mentor-video-viraj-email-172-7&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+172-7&utm_content_name=Father+of+2+discovers+new+family-flexible+career&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

-Jay Shetty, Jay Shetty Certification School ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/mentor-coaching-11/?el=mentor-video-viraj-email-172-7&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+172-7&utm_content_name=Father+of+2+discovers+new+family-flexible+career&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

column7: Feel like you’re capable of more?
column9:
Hey Candace,

Can I ask you a personal question?

On a scale of 1-10, how do you feel about your life right now?

* Your health?
* Your relationships?
* Your bank balance?

If it’s less then 8/10, then here’s a harsh truth:

************************************
It’s because you aren’t good enough.
************************************

Now, if this offends you, then go ahead and delete this email
because the rest of this is for people who are finally ready to
make a change.

.

…

…..

Are you still reading? Then props to you for being here!

Now, don’t get me wrong—if you’ve scored below 8/10, it isn’t
because you aren’t “worthy” of more.

Because, the truth is, you are.

But to get that score above 8/10, you need are to get better at a
certain set of skills.

The good news is these skills:

* Are trainable
* Can be learned
* And are easy to acquire

This should flood you with confidence, drive, and fire you up to
take the first step to making your life easier:

​
Now you might be asking:

“What skills, Dickie?”

Well, I’m not here to teach you about health or relationships…

But I can help you boost your bank balance.
-------------------------------------------

If you master:

* Sales
* Writing
* Marketing

Then these skills, in some shape or form, will make it easier for
you to earn more money.

The problem?

You can’t “learn” these skills by watching YouTube or reading
about them. To monetize them fully, you need a vehicle to
practice.

​
And I’m willing to bet you considered other “business” models to
practice these skills:

* Dropshipping?
* Affiliate marketing?
* Investing in crypto?

But these take tons of time, need some kind of start up capital
(especially crypto!), or require you to spend hundreds (if not
thousands of dollars) on ads.

(And trust us, spending money on ads when you have no idea what
you’re doing is like setting money on fire.)

But ghostwriting?

Ghostwriting is the easiest way to master and monetize these
skills—and get paid a premium to do so!

**********************************************************
The truth is, you probably won’t be a ghostwriter forever.
**********************************************************

I wasn’t. And Cole wasn’t. But it taught us the skills we needed
to build a 7-figure digital business and we wouldn’t have swapped
what we learned for anything.

We know the skills we mastered as Premium Ghostwriters will be
with us forever and we can use them wherever our current business
takes us, or if we decide to start a new one, or if everything
collapsed around us and we had to start from scratch tomorrow.

And by choosing ghostwriting, you can do the same.

So, are you ready to master the skills you need to future-proof
yourself (and finally get the life score you want)?

-----------------------------------------------------------------
​Click here to take the next step (and take your bank balance to
level 10). (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/38u4gzzkl4ckho836gpcrh4n98pnns7/x0hg5w7dh3uwvgqr67sg/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucHJlbWl1bWdob3N0d3JpdGluZ2FjYWRlbXkuY29tL2tpY2tzdGFydGVyLWNhbGw_ZWw9TndfT2N0MjEmaGU9YWljb2FjaGluZzIwMjUlNDBnbWFpbC5jb20=
)​
-----------------------------------------------------------------

-Dickie

Co-founder, Premium Ghostwriting Academy

PS… Think you can learn these skills on your own?

Then by all means give it a try!

But if you want to avoid all the mistakes Cole and I made along
the way (and build a profitable ghostwriting business as quickly
as possible), then we’d love to be your mentors inside PGA.

If you think:

• Your niche is saturated
• The competition is too strong
• And your business is rapidly dying

Then I have some good news:

Your niche *isn't* the problem. The problem is you're on the Genius-Idiot Rollercoaster (and you don't know it).

So, this week, I recorded a video explaining exactly how to ride it (and what it *actually* means about your business).

Check it out here: https://tapthe.link/Lj53QOQY7

And if you find it helpful, please let me know in the YouTube comments what your biggest takeaway was—would love to hear it!

Chat soon,

Their attention is easily captured by international league tables, pitting their country against others on one metric or another. The Global Innovation Index by the World Intellectual Property Organisation is one such measure. It aims to identify the world’s most innovative countries, drawing on more than 70 indicators, such as patents, high-tech exports and research spending. Because many of its indicators are adjusted for population or economic size, even small places have a fighting chance of climbing up the table. AI Snacks p*

Bite-sized AI news, fresh daily





Hey Snackers,
B
OpenAI just dropped GPT-5-Codex, a coding model that can now "think" about your broken code for up to seven hours straight - which
is approximately 6 hours and 59 minutes longer than most human developers before they rage-quit and blame the compiler. The new
version is rolling out to developers who presumably have the patience to wait for an AI to contemplate their spaghetti code longer
than it takes to fly from New York to London.
B
Meanwhile, Alphabet casually joined the $3 trillion market cap club, riding high on AI hype and a court ruling that basically said
"yeah, you're a monopoly, but the stock market doesn't care."
B
Speaking of trillion-dollar companies doing trillion-dollar things, Google launched something called the Agent Payments Protocol
(AP2) - essentially teaching AI how to spend your money for you. Because what could possibly go wrong with giving a
hallucination-prone language model access to your credit card?




p! Big on AI? Not Big on Spending?

 * Galaxy.ai is the world's #1 AI platform with 3000+ AI tools (everythingbfrom text to video) at one place for just $15/mo

 * p, ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Grok, Llama, Perplexity, DeepSeek

 * p( Midjourney, Ideogram, Leonardo, Stable Diffusion, DALLB7E 3, Flux, Nano Banana, GPT-Image

 * p, Veo 3, Luma, Kling, Pika, HeyGen, RunwayML, Hailuo (Minimax)

 * p5 ElevenLabs, Lyria, Hedra, CassetteAI

 * p Works seamlessly on web, iOS, and Android

 * p	 Join millions who have switched to Galaxy.ai [https://galaxy.ai]



SILICON VALLEY HUNGER GAMES
[https://www.reuters.com/business/online-marketplace-fiverr-lay-off-30-workforce-ai-push-2025-09-15/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]


Fiverr fires 30% of humans to become "AI-first"

B
In what might be the most on-the-nose example of AI eating jobs since the invention of the self-checkout kiosk, freelance
marketplace Fiverr just laid off 250 employees - that's 30% of its entire workforce - in a bid to become an "AI-first company."
B
CEO Micha Kaufman delivered the news with the kind of corporate speak that would make ChatGPT proud, explaining the company needs
to be "leaner and faster" - which is executive-speak for "we're replacing you with Python scripts."
B
The irony here is delicious: a platform built on connecting human freelancers with clients is now firing its own humans to
automate everything with AI. It's like watching a snake eat its own tail, except the snake has a Stanford MBA and stock options.
B
 * The company claims this will help them "leverage AI to automate systems" - translation: they're building bots to manage the
   bots that will eventually replace the freelancers.

 * This comes as Fiverr's stock has been struggling, down significantly from its pandemic highs when everyone thought they'd
   become a TikTok influencer.

 * The remaining 70% of employees are presumably updating their LinkedIn profiles with "AI prompt engineer" as we speak.

B
THE TAKEAWAY
Fiverr's move is the canary in the coal mine for the gig economy. If a company whose entire business model depends on human
creativity and skills is going all-in on AI, what does that say about everyone else? We're speedrunning towards a future where the
only jobs left will be "AI whisperer" and "person who turns the AI off and on again when it breaks."



NOTHING VENTURED, NOTHING GAINED
[https://techcrunch.com/2025/09/15/nothing-closes-200m-series-c-led-by-tiger-global-plans-ai-first-device-launch/?prefer_reader_view=1&prefer_safari=1&utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]


Smartphone startup raises $200M to build an "AI-first" device nobody asked for

B
Remember Nothing? The smartphone company founded by OnePlus co-founder Carl Pei that makes phones with blinking lights on the
back? Well, they just convinced investors to hand over $200 million at a $1.3 billion valuation to build an "AI-first device."
B
The company plans to launch this mysterious AI gadget next year, promising an operating system with "deep AI integration" - which
sounds suspiciously like every other smartphone released in 2025, except this one will probably have RGB lighting.
B
 * This comes after the spectacular failure of Humane's AI Pin, which proved that consumers don't actually want to wear a $700 AI
   brooch that projects a laser onto their palm.

 * Nothing's current phones are basically Android devices with a transparent back and some LEDs - revolutionary stuff.

 * The company claims they're building something "fundamentally different" but won't say what, which is the hardware equivalent of
   "trust me bro."

B
Investors are apparently still drunk on AI hopium, willing to throw money at anything with "AI-first" in the pitch deck. At this
rate, someone could raise a Series A for an AI-powered paperclip.
B
THE TAKEAWAY
The fact that Nothing can raise $200 million for vaporware while actual AI companies struggle to find product-market fit tells you
everything about the current state of tech investing. We're in the "throw money at anything with AI in the name" phase of the
bubble, which historically ends well for exactly nobody except the founders who cash out early.



CORPORATE SHOPPING SPREE
[https://www.reuters.com/business/workday-acquire-ai-firm-sana-11-billion-2025-09-16/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]


Workday drops $1.1B on AI firm because buying innovation is easier than building it

B
HR software giant Workday just announced it's acquiring Sana, an AI automation company, for $1.1 billion - proving once again that
when big tech companies need innovation, they just open their checkbooks.
B
Sana builds "AI agents to automate tasks," which is the most generic description possible but apparently worth a billion dollars
in 2025. The acquisition is part of a feeding frenzy where every enterprise software company is desperately buying AI startups to
sprinkle some machine learning fairy dust on their decades-old codebases.
B
 * This follows similar acquisitions by SAP, Oracle, and basically every other enterprise software dinosaur trying to stay
   relevant.

 * Workday's stock barely moved on the news, suggesting investors are as excited about this as employees are about mandatory HR
   training.

 * The real winners here are Sana's VCs, who turned a few million into a billion faster than you can say "synergistic AI
   transformation."

B
THE TAKEAWAY
The enterprise software M&A market has become a game of musical chairs where everyone's scrambling to buy an AI company before the
music stops. At this rate, there won't be any AI startups left to acquire by 2026 - just a bunch of bloated enterprise companies
with hastily integrated chatbots calling themselves "AI-native."



THE BEST THING WE READ TODAY [https://openai.com/index/how-people-are-using-chatgpt/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]


OpenAI accidentally reveals ChatGPT is mostly used for cheating on homework

B
OpenAI released a massive study on how people actually use ChatGPT, and surprise surprise - it's not for building AGI or solving
climate change. Most people use it for "getting information" (aka Googling with extra steps) and about 30% of consumer use is
work-related (aka making their boss think they're productive).
B
The study found that the early gender gap has "nearly closed," which is corporate speak for "everyone's equally lazy now." The
most telling stat? People are using it for "everyday practical tasks" - translation: nobody wants to write their own emails
anymore.
B
What's fascinating is that this comprehensive look at ChatGPT usage confirms what we all suspected: AI isn't revolutionizing human
intelligence; it's just making it easier to fake having any.




What else we're Snackin'

 * YouTube is giving Shorts creators access to Google's Veo 3 text-to-video model because apparently humans making content is so
   2024 (source)
   [https://techcrunch.com/2025/09/16/youtube-announces-new-generative-ai-tools-for-shorts-creators/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]

 * YouTube also launched AI tools for podcasters to create viral clips, solving a problem nobody knew existed (source)
   [https://techcrunch.com/2025/09/16/youtube-to-use-ai-to-help-podcasters-promote-themselves-with-clips-and-shorts/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]

 * Anthropic's new report shows AI adoption is concentrated in rich countries, shocking absolutely no one (source)
   [https://www.anthropic.com/research/anthropic-economic-index-september-2025-report?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]

 * YC-backed Rulebase raised $2.1 million to build an "AI coworker" for fintech compliance, the most boring use of AI yet (source)
   [https://techcrunch.com/2025/09/16/y-combinator-backed-rulebase-wants-to-be-the-ai-coworker-for-fintech/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]

 * "The Morning Show" is tackling deepfakes this season, with Jennifer Aniston and Reese Witherspoon playing themselves but
   concerned about AI (source)
   [https://techcrunch.com/2025/09/16/the-morning-show-makes-mission-critique-ai-new-season-2025-09-16/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]

 * The Agent Payments Protocol has Mastercard and PayPal on board, because teaching AI to spend money is definitely what humanity
   needs right now (source)
   [https://techcrunch.com/2025/09/16/google-launches-new-protocol-for-agent-driven-purchases/?utm_source=galaxy.ai&utm_medium=newsletter]

 * Studies show 77% of business AI use is for automation rather than collaboration, confirming that companies prefer robots to
   humans (source)

Kaggle


Hello Candace,

🎒 Today's Assignments

1. Complete the Intro Unit – “Foundational Large Language Models & TextGeneration”:


Listen to the summary podcast episode for this unit.
To complement the podcast, read the “Foundational Large Language Models &Text Generation” whitepaper.

2. Complete Unit 1 – “Prompt Engineering”:


Listen to the summary podcast episode for this unit.
To complement the podcast, read the “Prompt Engineering” whitepaper.
Complete these codelabs on Kaggle:

Prompting fundamentals
Evaluation and structured data

Make sure you phone verify your Kaggle account before starting, it'snecessary for the codelabs.
Want to have an interactive conversation? Try adding the whitepapers toNotebookLM.

💡 What You'll Learn

Today you'll explore the evolution of LLMs, from transformers to techniqueslike fine-tuning and inference acceleration. You'll also get trained in theart of prompt engineering for optimal LLM interaction and evaluating LLMs.

The first codelab will walk you through getting started with the Gemini 2.0API and cover several prompt techniques including how different parametersimpact the prompts. In the second codelab, you will also learn how toevaluate the response of LLMs using autoraters and structured output.

📋 Reminders


Tomorrow at 11:00 AM PT, Paige Bailey is hosting the first livestream onour YouTube channel to discuss the assignments with the course authors andother special guests from Google. Tomorrow's guests are Warren Barkley,Logan Kilpatrick, Kieran Milan, Anant Nawalgaria, Irina Sigler and MatVelloso.
Discord is the best place to ask questions – specifically in the#5dgai-question-forum channel. In addition to other participants, severalGooglers are there to help. During the livestream, we'll also pick somequestions from Discord to discuss. You'll get Kaggle swag if your questionis chosen!
We also have a troubleshooting guide for the codelabs. Be sure to checkthere for solutions to common problems.
We want this course community to be positive and supportive. Please followKaggle's community guidelines found here.

Happy learning and see you tomorrow!

The Kaggle Team

The Economist ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=f455644817a71033b46bc743cfad2641f64103125619baebdf40c3e26d53622ea985aec90aaeda534cd3f4dbac9704083b2080b64c528e0e64b9d8cf5777bb80 https://view.e.economist.com/?qs=5d00d2077c17b52b9b28281ee1b1da4a562d3e0ef96dfb513ffee4253599f5483a7b76c563dc809ef5846199db580ec32900a667cac0cd3e3703b1db8c402e34f2e8ec10d363917743f118787563835e Read in browser October 12th 2025 The Economist today A Sunday edition of our daily newsletter https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=f455644817a71033f88358769fe08fbd040c97cb3be61b25a08f48f54b0baa9a953acb276432b902a0ddf9413d15067c910bcb696484c1ea6703325bb32b9f4c https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=f455644817a71033f6d3aaa975efbca6525157daed16724ba075aaed761eb956565f9eff9a33410c5d7a83f059061aefc9275f691b495556718bbb9cd247555d https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=f455644817a71033e3cabb5f0fdda582b13f0dd4e46ef6c902135e50ca6551c57f20cbc37a60e9d1d4f6afa5c3604f5076749357488ebfd4 Adam Roberts https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=f455644817a71033e3cabb5f0fdda582b13f0dd4e46ef6c902135e50ca6551c57f20cbc37a60e9d1d4f6afa5c3604f5076749357488ebfd4 Digital editor Hello from London, What is the greatest division between America and Europe? You might think it is over attitudes to food or sport, policy towards China or something about the guardrails needed for capitalism. Not a bit of it. The biggest split is over cars. Americans expect to drive huge ones, ideally something that has the heft and noise of an elephant. Europeans are far likelier to opt for smaller beasts. When an American friend once visited, renting a stylish but tiny Fiat 500 at the airport, his teenage daughter was mortified, announcing it was obviously a toy vehicle and not fit for the road. Admittedly, Europeans are also driving bigger cars than they used to https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=f455644817a71033f7ac0cc23ec2dcef4cbba147cdb798ef98e00b416c886c85c9ef45fda5cabddfd04195358c6cebce0c580df48c271ed2 . But Americans increasingly prefer monsters, relishing the thrill of revving up a big truck and judging that, for drivers and their passengers, bigger vehicles bring more safety. Unfortunately, as we set out in a new article published this weekend https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=f455644817a71033f7f88a10feb7064f795d63f55f823f8b7c7336f8b276b6e45b25da4320e9c06e571239e654707fbf64d306a1e39c6cc2 , this is becoming a fatal trend for others on or near the road. The monsters increasingly flatten pedestrians, cyclists and drivers of smaller cars. Last year one pollster noted that 41% of Americans thought SUVs and pickup trucks had grown too big. Too right. Germany is on our minds today. State elections in the east of the country are usually not of huge interest to outsiders, but the two held today help to show how strong extremists are becoming in the political system. The hard-right Alternative for Germany, which stirs up support on the back of hostility to refugees and other migrants, looks to have come top https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=f455644817a710339483d3a3eab318ef41ac11df38aa6790d7b77541771dba02c24a15271d03be2eade6d948994531c6875ef3882ac8bd25 in Thuringia and appears to have run the conservative Christian Democratic Union close in Saxony—though it won’t be in government in either state. On the hard left, the party of Sahra Wagenknecht, a pro-Russian opposition leader who is hostile to migrants, seems to have come third in both places. (Read our weekend profile of Ms Wagenknecht. https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=f455644817a71033caf9380cd2310c304fc19d6846cdafdb8d910aaf057fc20b069a1028b898fd04e7a8d788b11040758e61d9fd8acb1fc4 ) Our latest Dateline history quiz is now live. Do you remember the year DVDs were launched? Or when Jack the Ripper prowled the streets of London? I certainly didn’t. Finally, our caption competition has been drawing you in in ever greater numbers. Thank you all for voting and for your suggested captions. This week I’ve chosen an image that we used on our cover in 2017. Back then we asked whether social media posed a threat to democracy. What caption would you write for it, or Mark Zuckerberg, today? Write to me at economisttoday@economist.com mailto:economisttoday@economist.com?subject=Caption%20context . Last week we asked you to vote on a shortlist of three suggestions for an image of an overstretched businessman. The winners, by a long stretch, were Keith Parr, David Paterson and Jim, who all proposed “Elon-gated”. Finally, we now want your votes on which of the following three ideas work best with the image, below, of Kamala Harris. column7: “Is PGA running a Black Friday campaign this year?”
column9:
Here’s a question we always get around this time of year:

“Is PGA running a Black Friday campaign this year?”

Valid question!

But before we tell you whether we are or not, let me tell you a
quick story…

*********************
The Tale Of 2 Writers
*********************

The first was a fuzzy-haired, scraggly-looking bargain hunter.

And when Black Friday came around, do you know what he did?

He set an alarm bright and early, and spent the entire morning
scrolling Amazon:

* “Oh! A coffee maker is on sale!”
* “Oh! A discounted television!”
* “Oh! A half-price vacuum!”

By the end of the day, he’d spent almost all his savings.

And a few days later, all sorts of gadgets and widgets and
plastic goods showed up in his living room.

And he was so excited…

For about a day and a half!

Then the novelty wore off. And a month later, he stopped using
his coffee maker and went right back to buying Starbucks every
morning. And a few months after that, the vacuum broke. And a
year later, he was waiting for Black Friday again… ready to spend
his hard-earned savings re-buying the same things as last year,
just their newest versions.

Forever spending, spending, spending.

But the second writer was different.
------------------------------------

She had completely forgotten Black Friday was coming up!

(That’s how little she thought about spending money on material
things.)

Instead, she spent all her time asking herself:

* “What skills do I need to acquire to increase my earning
potential?”
* “Who do I need to surround myself with to accelerate my
growth?”
* “How can I invest in myself NOW—that will make my future-self
happy?”

And while all her friends were wasting their money on televisions
and vacuums and widget-spinners on Black Friday, she reminded
herself none of those purchases were going to have an impact on
her REAL goals.

So instead, she decided to take her hard-earned money and invest
it.

In who?

In herself.

*****************************************************************
So, are we running a Black Friday discount for our Premium
Ghostwriting Academy?
*****************************************************************

Here’s the answer:

Nope—we’re NOT running a Black Friday discount for PGA.

Want to know why?

Because as of right now, PGA is actually very underpriced.

See, over the past few months alone, we’ve made tons of upgrades
to PGA.

We’ve added:

* 10+ new modules
* Dedicated success coaches
* 1:1 onboarding & coaching calls
* Personalized outreach & sales call reviews
* New group calls for additional support & accountability
* Etc.

And the single biggest piece of feedback we’ve been getting is:
---------------------------------------------------------------

“You guys are not charging enough for this program.”

That’s why we’re seriously considering to raise the price to join
PGA over the next few months.

Which means, if you’re actually looking to invest in yourself &
build the skills you need to:

* Monetize your skills as a writer
* Build a lucrative writing side hustle
* Escape your unfulfilling full-time job
* And finally enjoy the time & location freedom you’ve been
looking for

Then this is the best time to join PGA.

The question is:

---------------------------------------------
Which of these 2 writers are you going to be?
---------------------------------------------

Are you going to spend your hard-earned savings buying plastic
widgets you don’t need?

Or are you going to invest in yourself, your skills, and your
growth—so you can put yourself in a completely different
trajectory over the next year?

We hope it’s the latter.

But we like to share these examples to show that if you’re

You're receiving this email because we've made some important updates to our Terms of Service ( https://www.heygen.com/terms?utm_campaign=GDPR+remainders&utm_content=GDPR+remainders&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customerio ) and Privacy Policy ( https://www.heygen.com/policy?utm_campaign=GDPR+remainders&utm_content=GDPR+remainders&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customerio ).

HeyGen is committed to the safety and privacy of your data. We've update these documents to comply with the EU-US Data Privacy Framework. This includes important updates to the following sections of our Terms of Service and Privacy Policy:

*
The privacy policy is applicable to our recently launched mobile app.
* The certification for and registry in the EU-US Data Privacy Framework as a relevant mechanism for the personal data transfers to the United States.
* Greater clarification of legal bases for processing and purposes of processing.
* An introduction to third-party and alternative dispute resolution mechanisms regarding processing of personal data.
* More information about Data Protection Officer.
* And finally, information about relevant data protection authorities in the EU, UK and Switzerland.

LEARN MORE HERE ( https://www.heygen.com/terms?utm_campaign=GDPR+remainders&utm_content=GDPR+remainders&utm_medium=email_action&utm_source=customerio )
This information is provided to you to account for how we process data and to be transparent in our relationship with you. We value the trust you bestow on us when we process your data.

Hi Candace, 

Getting started with a new platform can be daunting, but having the right resources makes those initial experiences so much easier. 

Luckily, you have access to Heroku resources through Trailhead, the fun and interactive learning platform from Salesforce. It's the perfect way to build your skills and confidence before deploying your app on Heroku. 

How Trailhead Can Help You Understand Heroku

Guided Learning : Trailhead offers step-by-step trails and modules that teach you the fundamentals of app development and cloud technologies. Hands-On Projects : Put your new skills into practice with interactive challenges and projects. Gamified Experience : Earn points, badges, and super badges as you complete modules. It makes learning fun and rewarding. Free and Accessible : Trailhead is open to everyone, so you can learn at your own pace and on your own time. 

Get Started with Heroku on Trailhead

Develop Apps with Heroku Trail: [https://hello.heroku.com/e/36622/ent-trail-id-heroku-enterprise/m6b524/1305720190/h/V0L6iMwJ53HJ_psNXl9KkURJ0ue2BEh3lAt0Qsu2XnU] : Learn how to build and deploy apps on Heroku using your favorite programming languages and frameworks. Heroku Enterprise Basics: [https://hello.heroku.com/e/36622/dules-heroku-enterprise-baiscs/m6b527/1305720190/h/V0L6iMwJ53HJ_psNXl9KkURJ0ue2BEh3lAt0Qsu2XnU] : Explore the key features of Heroku Enterprise and how it can be beneficial to your business. 

Once you've completed these trails, you'll be well-equipped to deploy your app on Heroku and take advantage of all its powerful features. 

If you have any questions or need further assistance, don't hesitate to contact our support team: [https://hello.heroku.com/e/36622/contact/m6b52b/1305720190/h/V0L6iMwJ53HJ_psNXl9KkURJ0ue2BEh3lAt0Qsu2XnU] . 

Happy learning! 

The Heroku Team

Most people looking to land their first ghostwriting client
believe their bottleneck to securing their first deal is their
writing ability.

This means they end up:

* Reading more books on writing.
* Dropping another $750 on a writing course.
* Dedicating more time to improving their craft (at the expense
of learning other, non-writing skills).

Now, you have to be somewhat competent as a writer to charge for
your work.

But if you think getting better and better at writing will mean
people will pay you more, then I’ve got a rude awakening for you.
Because to make more money as a ghostwriter is not just about
improving as a writer.

It’s about all the other skills that surround the writing that
make your clients feel valued, heard, and comfortable which turn
you into a profitable ghostwriter.

Let’s dive into the 5 non-writing skills you need to master.

Prefer to watch rather than read? Click here to watch this as a
video on YouTube. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/zlu25ddl02bnh4mz667fphw09qg00c6/3ohphdu754me7vup/aHR0cHM6Ly95b3V0dS5iZS94eTJFTERzZFNWWT9zaT0yLUlGVUVwVjZWa1JlVHNq
)​

(
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/zlu25ddl02bnh4mz667fphw09qg00c6/3ohphdu754me7vup/aHR0cHM6Ly95b3V0dS5iZS94eTJFTERzZFNWWT9zaT0yLUlGVUVwVjZWa1JlVHNq
)​

*****************************************************************
Master these 5 non-writing skills to become a dangerously
profitable writer.
*****************************************************************

* Skill #1: Free Consulting. If you can’t help people for free by
giving them the strategy, you will never be able to charge for
your expertise. Free consulting is how you EDUCATE your way to
landing paying clients, not trying to force them into buying
something they don’t want. You should be able to show you
understand the problems they have, the outcomes they care about,
and the transformation they want to experience. But if you want
to learn about more how to use Free Consulting to grow your
writing business, make sure to check out this video. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/zlu25ddl02bnh4mz667fphw09qg00c6/n2hohqu396qz32a0/aHR0cHM6Ly95b3V0dS5iZS9jSFhmNFpKZk8tWT9zaT13QzdhXzRDOS1LTDhmS1FP
)​
​
* Skill #2: Sales. So many writers resist this, but there’s no
other way around it. You have to learn how to sell. Every
ghostwriter I’ve coached inside PGA makes a ton of money because
they learn the art of sales. This isn’t “selling out”—it’s about
helping someone out with the services you provide, not “cheating”
them out of money. But if this is something you struggle with, I
highly recommend checking out this video where I break down the
exact sales script I used to generate $3,000,000 worth of revenue
(
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/zlu25ddl02bnh4mz667fphw09qg00c6/48hvh7urd6l4rvbq/aHR0cHM6Ly95b3V0dS5iZS9QQW1tbU1XMnRkST9zaT1lYmdHeVcyd1NXYnhyOHJS
) for my ghostwriting agency.
​
* Skill #3: Account Management. This is about how you interact
with the client at every stage of the relationship—from sales to
project completion. The art of account management boils down to
doing a good job of anticipating the client’s needs. You want the
customer to go, “Wow, you held my hand and you were so attentive
that you’re the only person I want to work with, I couldn’t
imagine trying to find someone who is as attentive as you.” But
if you're new to account management & client fulfillment, check
out this quick deep dive breaking down how to onboard new clients
like a pro. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/zlu25ddl02bnh4mz667fphw09qg00c6/wnh2h6uw2x7ew7ul/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2tvb2wuY29tL2dob3N0d3JpdGVycy1hbm9ueW1vdXMvY2xhc3Nyb29tLzg5OTc1OGYxP21kPWVlZGQxNDAzZGNiOTRmNDg5ODE4YmNhYmE4NGJjYzVi
)​
​
* Skill #4: Understanding different business models. Part of what
allows you to charge more as a writer is figuring out the best
possible business model for your ghostwriting service. Are you
charging something that’s higher ticket where the person has to
pay in full? Or are you breaking up that payment into monthly
payments? Spend time studying the business side of pricing and
business models. But if you need some help getting started,
here's a great primer on the 8 most lucrative ghostwriting
services you can sell right now. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/zlu25ddl02bnh4mz667fphw09qg00c6/08hwhgud6ge3d5bp/aHR0cHM6Ly95b3V0dS5iZS9RcDNQQTlVVm5BVT9zaT02eHBuTFRHY2FkRHpJdlVv
)​
​
* Skill #5: Personal Branding. I think this is one of the most
misunderstood terms in all of marketing. You shouldn’t be aiming
to become known in “general.” Instead, aim to become known for a
niche (or category) that you own. Personal branding is about
evangelizing yourself BUT within a specific category. And the
most effective way to that, at scale, is by writing & sharing
your ideas online—consistently. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/zlu25ddl02bnh4mz667fphw09qg00c6/8ghqh3ul6qdml6fl/aHR0cHM6Ly95b3V0dS5iZS9lUnM1MEtyR0FtQT9zaT1BeUFrOVNwWDBNb2Q5eUU1
)​

Now, here’s the bottom line:

*****************************************************************
Not every day is going to be a writing day and not every day are
you going to feel like your writing is improving.
*****************************************************************

But that’s okay because all of these other skills are what allow
you to get ahead of 99% of other ghostwriters out there.

The big idea here is that writing is only a piece of the puzzle.
You can’t just spend all day crafting the best sentences and then
expect your:

* Your business to grow
* Your revenue to go up
* Your monthly earnings to become more stable and consistent
* And have people seeking you out instead of constantly grinding
to find your next gig

If you want all of these things to happen and if you want all of
these unfair advantages, you have to be willing to do things that
the average person is not willing to do.

And the average ghostwriter is not willing to do all of these
things—but a Premium Ghostwriter IS ready to do these things.

That’s it!

Cole

Co-Founder, Premium Ghostwriting Academy

column7: ⏰ A Simple Question That Changed My Perspective on Time
column9:
Hey friends,

Yesterday I shared the Magic Lamp journaling prompt - lots of
kind, inspiring replies to that email, so thank you to everyone
who replied with their own vision for what their answer to that
question would be.

Today I want to share another thought exercise / journaling
prompt to get your juices flowing while we’re in the midst of
“New Year New Me” energy.

This one comes from the YouTube channel / podcast Graham Cochrane
(
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn577zwf6h8lo4v00bg/wnh2h6uwldxvnxhl/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vQEdyYWhhbUNvY2hyYW5l
). I first came across Graham’s videos 8+ years ago when I was
first getting into trying to become a music YouTuber. The first
few videos I ever made were of me and my friends singing covers
of popular songs, and Graham’s YouTube channel Recording
Revolution (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn577zwf6h8lo4v00bg/reh8h9u0opwv4xi6/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vQHJlY29yZGluZ3Jldm9sdXRpb24=
) was helpful in teaching me about microphone positioning, audio
engineering, mixing and the like. Fast forward many years, and
now Graham’s pivoted into being a (rather good) business coach
instead of “the audio tutorial guy”. I binged a few episodes of
his podcast over the holidays and loved this simple question he
posed in one of them:

⁉️ What would you do differently if you didn’t feel you were
running out of time?

When I heard that, I paused the video, and let it sit for a few
moments. What would I do differently if didn’t feel like I was
running out of time? That question made me realise that I often
approach business (and sometimes even life) like I’m in a race
against some invisible clock. YouTube channel’s not growing as
fast as it used to. We could be launching products faster. Speed
of execution is important. I should get started with the next
book. I shouldn’t put more time into this video, I should just
get it out there. Etc.

I was listening to this episode while I was walking in the local
park, so I paused the video, opened up VoicePal (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn577zwf6h8lo4v00bg/08hwhgudp4gwvqbp/aHR0cHM6Ly92b2ljZXBhbC5tZQ==
), and recorded my thoughts in response to the prompt:

What would I do in my business if I didn’t feel like I was
running out of time? I would definitely take my time with product
launches. I wouldn’t worry so much about trying to film something
every day. Some days, like this one, I’d wake up, have a
leisurely morning, and explore until creative inspiration
strikes—like I did this morning for the productivity system.

If I wasn’t concerned about running out of time, I would focus on
making existing things better for our students rather than
constantly launching new things. I’d concentrate on really
understanding what our students want and need, then figure out
how to deliver it in a scalable way, like we’re doing with
Productivity Lab (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn577zwf6h8lo4v00bg/8ghqh3ul78qpzwal/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3NwYXJr
). I would be more hands-on with projects and take my time with
approvals, making sure I’ve thoroughly worked on offers before
launching them.

Right now, I aim to film about three things a week—sometimes even
trying to film daily. But I wouldn’t be wedded to doing two
videos per week if time wasn’t a concern. I would be comfortable
spending more time learning rather than just outputting content.

I think I would focus more intensely on how I can help people. If
I wasn’t concerned about running out of time, the true North Star
would be: Does this help our students achieve their dreams? Does
this actually help them build the life they want, achieve
financial freedom, or whatever their goal might be?

If I wasn’t trying to grow the business as fast as possible, I
would probably be more relaxed about hiring. I would focus on
building a base of recurring revenue where people are genuinely
delighted to pay each month or year.

I would prioritize life stuff more and go with my energy. On days
when I don’t feel like working, I wouldn’t force myself. If I
feel inspired on weekends, I might work then. It would be a more
fluid balance rather than trying to confine everything into rigid
structures.

I wouldn’t think of weekends as weekends or weekdays as workdays.
While still keeping some meetings on the calendar, I’d treat all
time as fluid exploration. Sometimes I might feel like doing
nothing or reading a book. Other times, I might want to watch
videos or play video games. And sometimes, when the energy is
right, I’d make YouTube videos, work on products, or build
frameworks. I would follow these natural rhythms if I wasn’t
concerned about running out of time.

Graham mentioned in the podcast that pretty much every business
owner he works with has this constant feeling that “time’s
running out”, “we’ve gotta move faster” etc. I certainly have
that - even though I’m the Feel-Good Productivity (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn577zwf6h8lo4v00bg/vqh3hmupq6e3llfw/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5mZWVsZ29vZHByb2R1Y3Rpdml0eS5jb20vYW1hem9u
) guy, and I’ve researched and written 3 chapters on the
importance of rest, energy conservation and burnout prevention, I
still often need to remember to take my own advice. It’s okay to
slow down sometimes. Time isn’t running out. We got this.

That’s not to say you should 100% always operate like this -
speed clearly has benefits. But as with most things, a virtue
taken to excess becomes a vice 😊

So I’ll put the question to you:

What would you do differently, in your work and/or life, if you
didn’t feel like you were running out of time?

Have a great week!

Ali xx

PS: Over the last few weeks, my friends and I built an app called
Superfocus (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn577zwf6h8lo4v00bg/m2h7h6u8lxm0vzcl/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdXBlcmZvY3VzLm1lLw==
) to help us be more focused and less distracted. It was
initially a side project, but we got some solid feedback and so
we want to launch it as a proper app soon. Check out the
walkthrough here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn577zwf6h8lo4v00bg/m2h7h6u8lxm0vzcl/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdXBlcmZvY3VzLm1lLw==
). If you like the idea, we’d love to have you as a Founding
Member, where you get lifetime access to the app at a steep
discount in return for giving us feedback and helping shape the
product. More info here if that sounds interesting (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn577zwf6h8lo4v00bg/m2h7h6u8lxm0vzcl/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdXBlcmZvY3VzLm1lLw==
) 😊

PPS: Even if I had all the time in the world, I’d still listen to
audiobooks at least at 1.5x speed - I just find that they’re more
enjoyable that way.

Kaggle







Hi Candace Grant,

As we approach the end of 2024, we reflect on a year of outstanding growthfor model publications on the Kaggle Model Hub. Our community hasconsistently raised the bar, pushing the boundaries of what's possible inmachine learning and AI. Even as the year draws to a close, there's been noslowdown—our model publishers have kept the momentum going strong withtheir incredible contributions.





PaliGemma 2
Publisher: Google
Based on Gemma 2 and SigLIP open components, PaliGemma 2
is a vision-language model with superior fine-tuning performance.
It excels at multilingual image-text tasks like captioning, object
detection, and visual QA.






Llama 3.3
Publisher: Meta
Llama 3.3 is a 70B LLM optimized for multilingual dialogue. It
leverages SFT and RLHF tuning to ensure exceptional performance,
safety, and helpfulness.






Phi 3.5
Publisher: Microsoft
A lightweight, open model family performant in reasoning and
instruction adherence, Phi-3.5 has a 128K token context and
advanced safety optimizations. Variants: Mini-instruct,
MoE-instruct, and Vision-instruct.






QwQ-32B-Preview
Publisher: Qwen / Alibaba
QwQ-32B-Preview, a 32.5B parameter causal language model
featuring 64 layers and a 32K token context. An experimental
model designed for advanced reasoning, it's ideal for math, coding,
and analytical tasks.






Gemini 2.0 Flash
Publisher: Google
Gemini 2.0 Flash is an experimental release with faster TTFT, enhanced
multimodal understanding, native image generation, and controllable
text-to-speech. It powers real-time vision and audio
streaming applications.





The past year was amazing, and we're tremendously excited to see what thecoming year is going to bring!

Brenda Flynn
Kaggle Partnerships Lead



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

)

https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/38uq72mkz3tkh26mkxxurh4k9opnns7/m2h7h6u8lledmwal/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3NwYXJr
)​

How Do I Access the Summit Recordings?

Recordings of all the workshops from the summit are only
available to those who purchase the VIP Package.

So, if you miss a session or are unable to attend for any reason,
upgrading to the VIP Package is the best way to catch up. Plus,
it comes with access to exclusive bonus workshops and other cool
perks too.

If you’d like to upgrade, you can do so after you've registered
for free (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/38uq72mkz3tkh26mkxxurh4k9opnns7/m2h7h6u8lledmwal/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3NwYXJr
).

​

What's Included in the VIP Package?

Here’s what you’ll get if you sign up to the VIP package:

🤖 Access to two exclusive bonus workshops on AI-Powered
Productivity with me;

📹 Access to all the recordings from every session from the
summit;

📝 Access to a resource bundle including an AI prompt cheatsheet
and other bonus resources that I use everyday to boost my
productivity;

💰 Plus, $97 off Productivity Lab membership if you join this
January.

​

When Are the Sessions?

The Productivity Spark Summit runs over two days - Saturday 4
January and Sunday 5 January - packed with actionable workshops
to help you kickstart 2025.

Each day runs from 14:00 to 19:15 GMT, with breaks between
sessions to keep you energised and ready to absorb every insight.

If you miss any of the live sessions, recordings are available
with the VIP Package.

​

What Sessions are Running?

On Saturday 4 January, we have:

🔮 The 2024 Reflection Workshop (14:00 – 15:30 GMT)

👑 Special Guest Workshop with TJ Power (15:45 – 16:45 GMT)

👑 Special Guest Workshop with Sahil Bloom (17:00 – 17:45 GMT)

🌅 Day #1 Wrap with Ali (17:45 – 18:00 GMT)

🚨 VIP Only: AI-Powered Productivity with Ali (18:15 – 19:15)

​

On Sunday 5 January, we have:

🎨 Sketch Your Future with Ali & Izzy (14:00 – 15:00 GMT)

🏗️ Design Your Most Productive Year Ever (15:15 – 16:45 GMT)

👑 Special Guest Workshop with Cal Newport (17:00 – 17:45 GMT)

🌅 Day #2 Wrap with Ali (17:45 – 18:00 GMT)

🚨 VIP Only: AI-Powered Productivity with Ali (18:15 – 19:15)

You can see more detail about each of the sessions here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/38uq72mkz3tkh26mkxxurh4k9opnns7/m2h7h6u8lledmwal/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3NwYXJr
).

​

How Do I Join the Sessions?

You'll be sent instructions on how to join the sessions once you
register for the summit.

We’ll also send you reminder emails throughout the weekend, so
you’ll always have the link handy.

For VIP attendees, exclusive session links will be emailed to you
and will also be accessible on Circle for easy access.

​

Who Are the Guest Speakers?

We’re thrilled to have an incredible lineup of guest speakers at
the Productivity Spark Summit, including:

Cal Neport

Author of Slow Productivity, Deep Work and Digital Minimalism,
Cal Newport is renowned for his groundbreaking insights into
focus and productivity in a distracted world. Get ready to learn
how to structure your time, energy, and attention to achieve more
with less effort.

Sahil Bloom

Entrepreneur, investor, and author of the upcoming book, The 5
Types of Wealth. Sahil is celebrated for his unique ability to
simplify complex ideas about business, personal growth, and
decision-making, captivating millions of people every week
through his social insights.

TJ Power

TJ Power is an esteemed neuroscientist, renowned international
speaker, and co-founder of Neurify, which specialises in
providing accessible and scientifically-backed teachings to
enhance the optimisation of human’s mental health.

​

Can I Invite a Friend to Join the Summit?

Absolutely!

We’d love for you to share the Productivity Spark Summit with
your friends. Taking action together is always more fun - and far
more effective 😜

Here’s how you can invite them:

1️⃣ Share this link: https://aliabdaal.com/spark (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/38uq72mkz3tkh26mkxxurh4k9opnns7/m2h7h6u8lledmwal/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3NwYXJr
)​

2️⃣ Tell them why you’re excited: Let them know what you’re
looking forward to and how the summit can help them kickstart
their goals.

3️⃣ Encourage them to join you: Accountability is powerful, and
doing this together could be the spark they need to make 2025
their best year yet

​

How Do I Get the Most out of the Summit?

The number one way to get the most out of the summit is to attend
the sessions live.

There’s nothing quite like experiencing the energy, insights, and
interactivity of live sessions - you’ll be able to engage with
the speakers, participate in Q&As, and connect with the community
in real time.

Here are a few additional tips to make the most of your
experience:

* Bring a Notebook: You’ll want to jot down insights and we’ll be
doing a bunch of exercises together too.
* Set Clear Goals: Think about what you want to achieve by
attending.
* Minimise Distractions: Create a quiet space where you can focus
during sessions.
* Review the Timetable: Plan your schedule around the sessions
you’re most excited about.

This is your opportunity to spark real momentum heading into 2025
💥

If you’ve got any more questions just hit reply and someone from
my team will get back to you as soon as they can.

I can’t wait to see you this weekend 🙂

Ali xx

column7: Join Us for the Learning Analytics and Artificial Intelligence M.S.Ed. (Online) Virtual Information Session!
column9:
February 27 | 7-8 PM

                                                               Learning Analytics and Artificial Intelligence (Online), M.S.Ed.

VIRTUAL INFORMATION SESSION




FEBRUARY


                                27                              




Thursday, February 27 | 7-8 PM (ET)
                                                               

                                Please join us for a virtual information session <https://apply.gse.upenn.edu/register/?id=d405eb09-6e76-4fdb-bec6-4e3f8edd9093&utm_campaign=LAAI_feb27&utm_medium=email&utm_source=invite> to learn about our Learning Analytics and Artificial Intelligence (Online) M.S.Ed. program.
                                                               

                                Discover insights into the program's curriculum, meet the instructors, and learn about admission requirements. This event is your opportunity to ask questions and find out how this program can help you achieve your educational and career goals.
                                                               

We hope to see you there!


RSVP <https://apply.gse.upenn.edu/register/?id=d405eb09-6e76-4fdb-bec6-4e3f8edd9093&utm_campaign=LAAI_feb27&utm_medium=email&utm_source=invite>
Whether we are researchers, teachers, administrators, or counselors, we are united in our mission to use the power of education to deliver new possibilities and drive more positive outcomes.





3700 Walnut Street
                              Philadelphia, PA 19104


This email was sent to aicoaching2025@gmail.com by Penn GSE Admissions & Financial Aid.
Unsubscribe from University of Pennsylvania Graduate School of Education. <https://apply.gse.upenn.edu/go?r=optout&mid=e5ae0238-9001-47a4-a3f7-ef2b93cb3654&utm_campaign=LAAI_feb27&utm_medium=email&utm_source=invite>

Hey Candace,

 

As promised, the first lesson of your “Pathway To Life Coaching” mini course is ready— click here to watch it now. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/jscs-pathway-day-1-funnel/?el=day-1-email-2-pathway-funnel&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D1E2+Pathway&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

In this video you’ll discover what life coaching is and what it takes to be successful.

Plus, I’ll explain how a life coach is different from a mentor, a therapist or a teacher.

This should help you decide if life coaching is the right path for you.

I’m so excited to be on this journey with you.

Let’s get started! ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/jscs-pathway-day-1-funnel/?el=day-1-email-2-pathway-funnel&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D1E2+Pathway&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

 

 

And by the way, if you prefer to read…

I’ve put the lesson into a PDF as well. Click here to download today's lesson book. ( https://drive.google.com/file/d/1PXYCz2RAm20Ci-BBqSS_j1DxiNIOEpyz/view?usp=sharing/?el=day-1-email-2-pathway-funnel&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+VSL%2FPathway+Funnel&utm_content_name=D1E2+Pathway&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

And I’ll be back, 4pm TOMORROW with your next lesson.

Enjoy!

-Jay Shetty, Jay Shetty Certification School

​
Hey there!

Two new template packs are now LIVE on Typeshare!

************************
Pack #1: Build In Public
************************

The internet has revolutionized how we learn and master skills.

Never before in the history of humanity has it been easier to
find the information you need to level up in your chosen field.

* If you want to learn how to cook, there’s an online course for
that.
* If you want to learn how to fly fish, there’s a YouTube channel
for that.
* If you want to understand the inner workings of Kurt Vonnegut’s
fiction plotting techniques, there’s an 𝕏 thread for that.

And part of the joy of writing online is sharing what you’re
learning as you work towards a particular goal.

Here’s an example from Dickie:

(
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ux37wnq4t0h4xg3m7cmhzw9r444tl/wnh2hghweqez8gs7/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9kaWNraWVidXNoL3N0YXR1cy8xODAxMjI2MDMyODI2OTcwNDQ0
)​
So, to help you a) share what you’re learning right now and b)
motivate those around to do the same, I created the Build In
Public template pack for you!

Here are the templates you get inside:

* The 30-Day Obsession: Document your intense focus on a specific
topic over 30 days, sharing daily updates, mistakes, learnings,
and metrics.
* The Encouraging One Liner: Reframe what people see as a
negative trait into something necessary to achieve your goal.
* Here's Why I'm Learning This Skill: Explain your unconventional
choice to focus on a specific skill, detailing the reasons behind
your decision and how it aligns with your goals.
* This Is What I Want (And How I Will Get There): Outline your
past achievement, your new goal, and a detailed step-by-step
framework to reach it.
* Stop Talking About Your Goals: More action, less chat (at least
with those who might bring you down!) Focus on executing and
sharing results rather than just talking about intentions.
* This Is How I'm Playing The Game: Briefly explain your strategy
for achieving a goal and your plans for after you've reached it.
* Here's Why You Haven't Started (Yet): Share common
misconceptions holding people back from a desired action and
provide a simple, actionable step to overcome them.

*********************************
Pack #2: Famous People As Content
*********************************

When was the last time a celebrity's rise to fame, an
entrepreneur's innovative breakthrough, or the tragic fall of a
well-known and popular figure caught your attention?

Probably only yesterday.

The truth is, these stories resonate with us on a deep level,
keep us entertained, and speak to universal human experiences. We
hope that by looking at those who have success (and those who
lost it) we can learn something to help us make change in our own
lives.

(
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/d0ux37wnq4t0h4xg3m7cmhzw9r444tl/8ghqhohlmom4kzbk/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9kaWNraWVidXNoL3N0YXR1cy8xODM0MjA2OTMxOTg2MDM4ODgx
)​
That’s why we created the “Famous People As Content” pack. It
will help you share those stories with your audience—and reach
more people, attract more readers to your work, and get more
views on your content.

Here are the templates you get inside:

* Person Who Changed Your Life: Share how a famous person's work
or example transformed your perspective, offering key lessons
that can reshape your audience's worldview.
* The Phoenix: Tell an inspiring comeback story of a well-known
figure, demonstrating how they overcame adversity to achieve
remarkable success against all odds.
* The Downfall: Trace the dramatic rise and fall of a prominent
person, illustrating the unpredictable nature of success and what
lessons can be taken from their example.
* Everyone Talks About These People: Introduce an unsung hero in
your field, revealing their game-changing technique or framework
that led to extraordinary results.
* The Best Quote: Break down a famous person's inspirational
quote into a practical, step-by-step guide for overcoming
challenges and achieving desired outcomes.

However, these weekly template packs are only available to
Typeshare Pro Writers.

column7: Best Practices for Simplifying Complex SQL
column9:
View this post on the web at https://seattledataguy.substack.com/p/best-practices-for-simplifying-complex

Hi, fellow future and current Data Leaders; Ben here 👋
Today, we will dig into an issue I have seen a lot. Those queries never seem to end.
You scroll and scroll, and yet they keep going!
Before we dive into the article, I’d also like to share about a free webinar I’ll be hosting alongside Richard Meng titled Unstructured Data, Structured Insights [ https://substack.com/redirect/16c2bca1-186f-4ccb-85ea-c8a8ab5b114e?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]. If you want to learn more about going beyond chatbots to get value out of unstructured data, you won’t want to miss out!
I hope to see you there.
With that out of the way, let’s jump into it!
Intro
Maybe you’re luckier than me.
Maybe you’ve never opened a .sql file or an Airflow [ https://substack.com/redirect/e897dfb2-5f65-4ef1-8d62-7861bdcac8f4?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] DAG only to be greeted by a 5,000+ line query—a true monster of a script that leaves you wondering where to begin.
I’ve seen plenty of these, and every time, I ask myself: Why in the world do these exist? And, more importantly, how can teams avoid them?
With tools like ChatGPT and Cursor making it easier than ever to generate SQL, I have a feeling we’ll see even more of these sprawling queries in the wild.
So, in this article, I’ll explore why massive SQL queries happen, why they’re a problem, and how you can break them down before they become unmanageable.
Why Should You Care?
Before we dive into why 5,000-line queries exist and how to avoid them, let’s talk about why they’re a problem in the first place.
Maintainability: Large queries are a nightmare to read, understand, and update. When a single SQL script stretches across thousands of lines, even the smallest tweak can have unintended consequences—turning debugging and refactoring into a frustrating game of whack-a-mole.
Data Quality [ https://substack.com/redirect/0e9919ee-d9ad-425a-9a5f-1267ef7f1559?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]: Ensuring data accuracy is already a challenge, but long analytical queries make it even harder. If bad data sneaks in—and if your query isn’t broken up—it might not fail until it’s well into the final 5,000-line query. Maybe you get lucky and catch it before production. If not? Good luck!
Where did it go wrong? The first CTE? The second subquery? The fifteenth case statement? If you’ve dealt with SQL error messages [ https://substack.com/redirect/fbc581ac-7c3d-4b2b-bc90-a415334fc0e3?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] before, you know they don’t always tell you where to start looking. And it’s even worse when the query technically runs but spits out bad data.
Evolution Over Time: SQL [ https://substack.com/redirect/ca81ffa8-30f6-49fe-8b78-a6f6861457c9?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] queries rarely start as behemoths. They grow—new fields, conditions, joins, and business requirements pile on over time. Without proper modularization, a once-simple query can quickly balloon into thousands of lines, becoming an unmanageable, tangled mess.
Why Do 5,000-Line Queries Exist And How Can You Avoid It?
No, really—why do 5,000-line SQL queries exist?...

Hi Candace,

Why should you give AI a try? Our tools are designed to help you work through repetitive day to day tasks so that you can focus on what’s most important.

Generate and edit

You can ask Notion AI to generate or edit your writing. Guide the response by @mention-ing style guide, project update, or a page of user feedback.

Analyze files

Notion AI can ‘see' PDFs and images. Upload a file to have Notion AI recommend a workback plan based on a proposal, or explain any image. Just click the 📎 icon!

Chat about anything

Leverage cutting-edge language models like GPT-4 and Claude, so you can (privately!) ask it about any topic. And it’s easy to add the response into your page—no need to copy/paste from a separate tab.

Search and find

Ask any question about your workspace to quickly find answers in from your Notion projects and documents.

Plus, in BETA for paid teams, AI connectors allows you to connect Slack and Google Drive so you can also search across your most important applications. GitHub, Jira, and more are coming soon!

Achieve more together

Google Workspace offers intuitive tools to streamline communication,simplify project management, and increase overall efficiency for teams ofany size.

Discover Google Workspace<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5p4ItFy8pu519hY8cR0S9GeppjfLeLgEzX3q90Jlu5pdPvjOtCKRCDtimd3KZoX16YiPBPrz29jHUlTPTaQAZcwILWFdAzLxaY2CEmBTBCHZjDgxAUS_oQmNwKITNRfZUkrXj-zU6WV_Yz8pqdIMqXV6Q4pGrQV5No>

Hi Candace,

Want to eliminate communication bottlenecks, share information seamlessly,and reach milestones with more speed? Here are some tips to make this kindof transformative collaboration a reality.

Organize team files in a shared space

Use shared drives to store your team’s work in secure, easy-to-manageshared spaces.

Create a shared drive<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5r6czNWOvqzHbgXpNopTDg_WyqqwxmHclrXjmmjCUtJt0kw_PMNArXqZXsbpmF2zFqLYmaHVi4mb0YExkeS_4UurdWxNrXC-q0ir8lyU3Ji2D_g4L8m-i1OZEf3RjL13keWSDNOBj1OonktYWiHOSK8PKmmI6se7kS2W0r4Mnm4wbKvP7YgP4nzYXNByYoZ1EjytzbBLk8FOQQPyw>

See real-time edits

With real-time presence, you can see who’s editing office files stored inDrive.

Learn more<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5qBkKcw4FDs4reLHQ0cowdJIGk9r2bnFPv239webPsuEOCD5xEqdECfFZJv_Ie39tfzvJyA7gGL9pamP9kjPvgsweLa4rDeoYJfhKKvtUaBXj_FpQiLq4uUSCJHZEBjRCAnP08b8-OEVEGy509o7QYxsVf-f99k1aHEg_uCVWTQ3BifThiuB3IGMd1oMeZSJYnT7ln1gy2QlibYey2loqGsjXkWMPFvKC4VWsyGZ12iaroNUrw4Ps8hR5OFw2KL2e4oHd35meNZynN_HTk392TBQavHZrrE>

column7: Introducing FACTS: Benchmark Your Model’s Factuality
column9:
Kaggle







Hi Candace Grant,

Large language models are revolutionizing access to information, butensuring their responses are factually accurate and grounded in sourcematerial remains a critical challenge.

To address this, we've partnered with Google DeepMind and Google Researchto launch FACTS, a benchmark and leaderboard for evaluating the factualgrounding of LLMs.





View the Leaderboard



FACTS evaluates models on their ability to deliver context-specific answersthat satisfy user requests. Responses are assessed on their factualaccuracy and adherence to the provided context.

Explore FACTS, access the public task dataset, and see how leading modelsperform on the leaderboard.

Happy Kaggling!

The Kaggle Team



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

I’ve taken my thick-knit, chocolate-brown cardigan out for a (frankly sweaty)
spin. I’ve watched “When Harry Met Sally… .” I’ve landed on a Halloween costume.
For weeks, I’ve tried and failed to conjure fall’s arrival here in New York,
where the high last weekend tipped well into the 80s.

But I think I know what did the trick, what finally summoned the chill in
today’s air. It was Dan Pelosi’s creamy tortellini soup
[https://nl.nytimes.com/f/cooking/enS-GwtLyJM3UWslprLPDA~~/AAAAARA~/kGx022iTKWzItuykfECpemiKXfuSkmOJH_loshy-6BpxmDT0KEG-yh0bBeokW2YQos8XFICJZ3mzN1RtGWgff2_AzGzRSUsP-mDvfmrGpjBnGYy1d4t_ctbPTo0wGJRzM_cP3Fcmd-AqIMhggBsmyHvaeKFjfm3TXPPqslDC1gahSPZwxPU2BMItEKcuyYjEx6W4J2-bNgFG6bGxs6Z2F9k46h3Sbl0eWT6fKF4M__hqInrXea4d5yBU00CpVJZ2AoJjPXOxWfqd1eT9P_D1xVNcos3pzhZcPHNiEEyn_eyi41iAsE4389q0UyO0F0DVFRZRAoXVPzO2XIRffCHzW25b_Lk8Xbii28sJs6ig7BejLxJBQKIj08Vr0q6vOYGn]
. This soup has had an iron grip on my group chat, weather be damned. One friend
made it on Saturday, influencing another to make it on Sunday, influencing
another to make it on Tuesday. These women willed soup season into existence
with the sheer power of a paprika-and-fennel-fragrant tomato broth.

I’m late to the party. But not for long. Dan’s recipe is for carnivores and
vegetarians alike. You may see sausage in the ingredients list, but it is
entirely optional. (“Does not need sausage at all honestly!” wrote one reader).
Feel free to skip it in favor of a can of white beans, a suggestion from my
girlfriends and at least one of the recipe’s commenters.

Dan’s soup is high on my soup bucket list, a catalog I’ve been keeping mentally
but will now formalize for you with this newsletter. It’s been too long since I
last made Alison Roman’s spicy noodle soup with mushrooms and herbs

column7: 🚀 The Most Powerful Way To Come Up With Video Ideas
column9:
Hey Candace,

Hope you’ve had a great week so far 🙌

Quick thing before we dive in - we’re running a Black Friday sale
on PTYA in a couple of weeks, so if you want to be amongst the
first to hear when the offer goes live, make sure you join the
waitlist by subscribing with one click here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/wvugd3nzo9bghkgrox7f7hnqzlzxxi8h4lw6v/7qhrxo68c2u9w5vgzkt9/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2NvbmZpcm1hdGlvbi9ibGFjay1mcmlkYXktd2FpdGxpc3QvP2VtYWlsPWFpY29hY2hpbmcyMDI1JTQwZ21haWwuY29t
).

Anyway, on with today’s email where I wanted to share one of the
most powerful techniques you can use when you’re stuck for new
video ideas: viral replication.

I know the term sounds a bit clinical, but the concept is
actually pretty straightforward: if you want to maximise your
chances of a video doing well, look at videos that have already
gone viral and take inspiration from certain elements that made
them successful.

Now this isn’t about copying content. Instead, viral replication
is about analysing what’s working in high-performing videos -
whether that be the title structure, thumbnail style, video
format, pacing, stuff like that - and then creating your own
original content that leverages those insights.

Let me show you what I mean with an example from one of our PTYA
members.

​Han Zhango’s (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/wvugd3nzo9bghkgrox7f7hnqzlzxxi8h4lw6v/9qhzhdudzrk796iz/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vQGhhbnpoYW5nbw==
) a Columbia University graduate who shares science, learning,
and self-improvement content. She joined PTYA back in 2023 and
has since grown to just under 250K subscribers.

One of Han’s most popular videos is called “Efficient studying:
how to learn so FAST it feels illegal” (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/wvugd3nzo9bghkgrox7f7hnqzlzxxi8h4lw6v/3ohphdu34g6wzrsp/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dD04MXMmdj0yZTBKeWZUaE90OA==
) and it’s got 457K views, which is super solid. Everything about
the video is unique to Han - her editing style, thumbnail, the
hook where she leans on her experience at a military-style
boarding school in China, and the value of the video - all except
the title.

​
This is actually a viral title formula that works incredibly well
across a bunch of different niches, even on very small channels
(with less than 20K subscribers), and you’ve probably seen
variations of it everywhere, so things like “How to make money so
fast it feels illegal” and “Change your life so fast it feels
illegal”.

But how do you actually make viral replication work for you?

Well, an easy way to get started is by looking at your top 10-20
competitors and sorting their videos by view count. Pick one
that’s done really well, and think about how you could create
your own version with your unique perspective and expertise.

But viral replication works even better when you find outlier
videos - videos with high views relative to the channel’s
subscriber count - and tools like VidIQ and 1of10 can help you
spot these pretty quickly.

For example, if a channel with only 15K subscribers has a video
that’s hit 500K views, that’s a massive outlier. It means they’ve
landed on something that resonated way beyond their existing
audience - so people clicked, watched a good chunk of it, and the
algorithm responded by pushing it out to more people.

Another tip when it comes to viral replication is to look beyond
your niche too. Some of the best ideas come from adapting
successful formats from completely different corners of YouTube,
just as we saw with the “How to [X] so fast it feels illegal”
title format.

With all that said, I’d be lying if I told you that viral
replication was bulletproof.

While it definitely increases your chances of success, it’s not a
guaranteed viral video generator. Your content still needs to be
genuinely good, unique to you, it needs to align with what your
audience actually wants to see, and there’s always an element of
timing and luck involved with YouTube too.

The timing point is especially important - if you’re leveraging a
trending idea or viral video that’s already been covered
endlessly by other creators in your particular niche, it might be
worth re-thinking and looking for an alternative. Otherwise, you
risk putting loads of effort into a video… only for it to totally
flop because you caught the wave too late.

It’s frustrating, but it’s also just part of the YouTube game.

So my actual advice would be to use viral replication as a
strategy, especially when you’re struggling with ideas or trying
to reach new audiences. But don’t make it your only strategy.

Consistency still matters way more than chasing viral hits, so
it’s way better to show up regularly with solid content that
serves your audience rather than burn yourself out trying to
crack the algorithm with every single video.

And remember to always, always put your own spin on things. Your
personal perspective, expertise, and personality are what’ll make
the content valuable, and it’ll always be so much better than a
watered-down copy of someone else’s video.

If you want to dive deeper into other ways to come up with ideas,
then there’s a whole module on this within PTYA, and don’t forget
to join the waitlist if you want to be amongst the first to hear
when our Black Friday offer goes live - click the link here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/wvugd3nzo9bghkgrox7f7hnqzlzxxi8h4lw6v/7qhrxo68c2u9w5vgzkt9/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2NvbmZpcm1hdGlvbi9ibGFjay1mcmlkYXktd2FpdGxpc3QvP2VtYWlsPWFpY29hY2hpbmcyMDI1JTQwZ21haWwuY29t
) so you don’t miss out.

Hope that was useful!

Talk soon,

Ali xx

P.S. In case you missed the announcement a few weeks back, we’re
currently looking for creators to join our UGC Accelerator
programme on our new platform, CreatorGrid. If this sounds
interesting, you can get more information and sign up here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/wvugd3nzo9bghkgrox7f7hnqzlzxxi8h4lw6v/n2hohquv60wdr5a0/aHR0cHM6Ly9nby5zcGFya2xlLnNvL2NuXzEy
).

🚀 Want to start a YouTube channel? Go here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/wvugd3nzo9bghkgrox7f7hnqzlzxxi8h4lw6v/48hvh7um68zognuq/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3BhcnQtdGltZS15b3V0dWJlci1hY2FkZW15
).

Update Your Email Preferences (

) | Unsubscribe from CreatorNotes (

Upskill effortlessly. Our bite-sized, expert-led IxDF Courses help you get
skills that make you valuable in any job, in any industry.

Learn directly from experts at NASA, Google, Adobe — with lessons you can binge
like Netflix.

Build your skills to build your salary potential.

Take IxDF Courses by the World's Best
[https://email.mailgun.interaction-design.org/c/eJx8zsGq2zAQheGnkXcNmpGl0Sy8KAS_RpHGM44g1w6y0_Txi-m23O3hwPcvE1tVy4NOQDFAyBnC8JgIKeeliIJq9KBMXLkWFgbwCXBo06K1VuEqlY1tEQEpJUnKLGZW1I2-baf2Imfbtx-LHm3dbntfh-f0OM_X4cJPh7PD-fP53P5_dTg_97VtDmdgIEIXZv3zal0PF-5XMUMafXaYui6tq5y_3v3pwv2fgPEy4qXE752Is-zvfujhMF1zOd9dXbgXK2aMmYyqjwUseU9aiVQzefNJTCoQ0RgIWDklLCAjez-amOLQp9JkL_Jo24oeoxv9-lXa8yb71_B7wr8BAAD__6wIeSA]
 3. BUILD YOUR NETWORK (AND YOUR NET WORTH!)
The IxDF Local Group in your city
[https://email.mailgun.interaction-design.org/c/eJxsyj1yhSAQB_DTQBeHD59CQZHGeyx_WN2ZJ2SUxMntc4H0v5Ii58pB12TXl7c-BOv1kYydGaWW2fnFBfDKtFA0IUePitVoSaXmnBEzcuTIBbAgWrCECGamqmYjbdSLMKS3j1Jv2dvUr12_0zHG1638p3KbctvzPNP_VLkN_Ty_m4xffSUSdMIhbXfGvdRs9pPkPaGf-ie5vwAAAP__lwpC1w]
