Warm and supportive atmosphere. Real human connections. In 495 cities in 103
countries.

From workshops, knowledge sharing and casual coffee meetups—this is where
valuable relationships, unexpected opportunities and lifelong friendships are
born.

Find Your IxDF Local Group
[https://email.mailgun.interaction-design.org/c/eJxsyj1yhSAQB_DTQBeHD59CQZHGeyx_WN2ZJ2SUxMntc4H0v5Ii58pB12TXl7c-BOv1kYydGaWW2fnFBfDKtFA0IUePitVoSaXmnBEzcuTIBbAgWrCECGamqmYjbdSLMKS3j1Jv2dvUr12_0zHG1638p3KbctvzPNP_VLkN_Ty_m4xffSUSdMIhbXfGvdRs9pPkPaGf-ie5vwAAAP__lwpC1w]
 4. BUILD YOUR INDUSTRY EDGE

forward-thinking professional. That way, you don't get left behind when managers
decide who to reward and promote.

You get 90% off all IxDF Master Classes. Choose from our on-demand library or an 
upcoming live session.

[https://email.mailgun.interaction-design.org/c/eJx8zrtqw0AQheGnWXU2e78UKgJGrxFmZmfkBVkyKznO4weRNqT-D3ynjkWQJQ88mhSccTkbN9xHJ1Sr0cYblJJc9OSDQHUFJXPVfmhjZUSkgoRFilQiQwCRYi4kIsDK67Ye3IGOtq2Xynub1-vW52EZ78fx3JX7UHZSdnq_39e_p8pOyza3VdnJFJOSVW7i72frvCt3Ox8XE73OysbOtXWm4_PVF-Vuv4INpxFOJfzvBDs9YD-4X2iBfedd2XhWOF6dlbtBzEmYLRVDwVcgZo1gfEEXTWRiLD7os2edvE7eIVKKOQgJEOahj9BoA7q3dbbaBuX1_IC2XGl7DF-j_QkAAP__GUZ8_Q]
 5. GET INSTANT CAREER HELP IN A SAFE, SUPPORTIVE SPACE
Join IxDF Community Conversations to connect with a global network of
like-minded professionals. Share ideas, get advice, and make connections that
could change your career.

Introduce yourself or ask a question — and watch the magic of the global IxDF
design community unfold.

Go From Zero to Hero in a Caring Community
[https://email.mailgun.interaction-design.org/c/eJx80M1q6zAQhuGrkXcn6F-jhRcHgm-jzIxGjsCxg-wkvfzidlu6fgee4StjriQVBhlNCs44AOOG2-h9rKBNRNI66MhaAA2VBImTQ8ShjUWIiDMx5ZprYTaMGDlC5lorivK6rYd05KNt678ie5vXy9bnYRlvx_HYlfuv7KTs9H6_L7-fKjst29xWZSeTTUpWuUk-H63Lrtz1_Dib6DUoG7uU1oWPj2dflLv-CDacRjiV8LcT7MTb-pK-49l2ZeMZ8Xh2Ue6aDESiYBP4mhKyrj7nEj24FKMrIcH3dppsMoaCAy-edARjImkGHPqIjTfkW1tnq21QXs93bMuFt_vwGu1XAAAA__9m1Xni]
 6. GET AN IXDF CAREER PROGRAM JUST FOR YOU
Get an IxDF Career Program tailored to your career goals: Instant help, and a
community laser-focused on zero overload, just clear-cut learning.

Learn lots, effortlessly. No fluff, no overwhelm.

Explore IxDF Career Programs
[https://email.mailgun.interaction-design.org/c/eJx8zr3K3DAQheGrkbss0uhnpMJFYHGdOwij8Ywt8Gcvsjebyw8mbUh7OPC881i0iuZBRofRO5-z88M6Bo2ArjpJbg5AHkOC6jV7VFfDbIc2zlJr5VK5Fi06MzsmSpxyYVUlMcG2_ZJOfLVj_zbL2Zb9cfRl2Mb1ul6n8d8NTAamz-fz-PfVwLQdS9sNTK44RDB-kt-v1uU0_nkXF5eCzQZSl7l14evnu2_GP_8KEG8j3kr8vxNh4uPdTzkNpHum693F-CcpqRbIqFhtJKfJWpSKKJLRqk2sXB0iBo-uSEkJyHEo1gZlFTDgN6G-t335Qdc69JEaH8Rr2xewEE2wyxe17cHH1_BrhD8BAAD__5jVfkQ]
 7. BUILD A PORTFOLIO. LAND YOUR DREAM JOB
Need experience? IxDF makes it easy for you to build your Design Portfolio so
you can show you have the hands-on skills to get hired. Or grow in your current
job.

Don't have any design experience? No problem! Thousands of members have done it.
You can too.

Build a Portfolio To Land Your Dream Job
[https://email.mailgun.interaction-design.org/c/eJxsyjFyhSAQANDTQIcDqxgoKNJ4D1h2lRm_-wf5McfPBdK_miIX4qApuS8_uzkEN-sjAUZY52LBF6wESwVnmf3ibXDBOdQtVSqlYCxYIkeuiA5zXnENEZk5k1psuwb1jKPJZSrdbb8m6bs-0zHG-1bzt4JNwfY8z_Q_VbChfPpNt4LtkMcMMdgpDzLZfH7NW_pgOZvonnJDyXi0awcLXi12f-V2Tigv_ZPgLwAA__886kxv]
 WHY IXDF?
 * IxDF helps you learn design and design your dream career.
 * Make yourself valuable. In any job. Any industry. Skills in design are not
   just for designers.
 * Great design makes your customers smile. More smiles = more profits = more
   salary potential for you.
 * Learn effortlessly from industry pros—from NASA, Google, Apple, Meta, and
   more.
 * Steal our insights. Present them as your own with our goldmine of 246
   downloadable templates.
 * Increase your salary potential and job opportunities when you show IxDF
   Certificates as credible evidence of your skills.
 * The world needs great design. Let's design a better world together!

column7: Competition Launch: BYU - Locating Bacterial Flagellar Motors 2025
column9:
Kaggle







Hi Candace Grant,

Macromolecular machines drive life at the microscopic scale, yetidentifying them remains a challenge. The flagellar motor, essential forbacterial motility, is one such structure - difficult to spot in 3Dreconstructions due to noise, variable orientations, and crowded cellularenvironments.

In this competition, you'll build ML models to scan 3D tomograms and spotflagellar motors in bacterial cells. Dive into the challenge and craft amodel that decodes complex 3D tomograms and illuminates the hidden enginesbehind bacterial movement.





Total Prizes:

$65,000


Entry Deadline:

May 28, 2025




Learn More



Your work could improve cryogenic electron tomography (cryo-ET) analysis,helping researchers study infectious diseases, develop new medicines, andadvance synthetic biology.

Good luck,

Walter Reade
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

column7: Changes to supported models in PartyRock, an Amazon Bedrock Playground
column9:
To view this email as a web page, go to the following address: https://pages.awscloud.com/index.php/email/emailWebview?mkt_tok=MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGWXyO5HSuYayncnP0RfvZVrFuxTcKMY_K9JCSxICB2hCoo1jCDSUKV_V-3qNnEwOaLpIJaGd_UGc0zf-zt4XmPwxSll3KeP1Zf37RcoZqGVkANgYbFxXPX6g

Anthropic’s Claude 2 is no longer available to use within PartyRock.


Hello PartyRock user,

This email confirms that Anthropic’s Claude 2 is no longer available to use within PartyRock. Anthropic’s Claude 3 models Haiku and Sonnet are available when building apps with PartyRock. For all users whose apps relied on Claude 2, those apps have been automatically updated to inference Claude 3. You can select from currently supported models when editing apps by selecting the edit button in the upper right corner of any AI powered widget in the model dropdown menu. 

To access your apps, visit PartyRock <https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGWXyO5HV06TwIx5k_cOUh5Mxzg2N2wIywRtKAvPIYQ2DYARQQtqFda3qF_A0vuZ62C0JwXQKA=>. 

Thanks,
The PartyRock Team

[https://click.calendly.com/wf/open?upn=u001.OQopjVvfRcQLxlQstZRu-2FxFO92-2Fx06uKqWPsd9Ap9hn3p08lIEYGVxobVEWJaOBXJHIeGFf0JllgiIHuimnO6LYR2Ae-2B0csHBII3fetPVB3yObAZxCpMwmCYfn7smbITyS-2F1Gcl4JGJbohpvFxgcKQ6MQqLKBQaM-2BJYsAUHHnCcTkjB4ikZ4E26T775zW0TLe-2BuYcNnko6592ShTTVyakEPY0F0FfE4GMDc8Pdei5uk-3D]

Hey Candace,

Last week, a few members of the team hopped on a flight from the UK to join me in Hong Kong for a few days of annual planning.

It’s not often we get to sit down in person, so we made the most of it and I think we’ve mapped out some pretty decent business goals for 2025.

There’s something I find really energising about hitting pause, taking a step back, and looking at the bigger picture. It’s easy to get caught up in the day-to-day grind, but having the space to think deeply about our vision and strategy feels like hitting the “reset” button.

One thing that struck me during the process was how much planning is about anticipating challenges. Whether it’s scaling the business, improving our processes, or tackling new projects, we constantly find ourselves asking, ”What could go wrong?”

And that’s where a brilliant psychological tool comes into play that I thought I’d talk about in this email: the premortem.

The idea of the premortem comes from psychologist Gary Klein, and it’s honestly a game-changer when it comes to planning and problem-solving.

Unlike a traditional postmortem — where you look back at what went wrong after everything’s already fallen apart — a premortem flips the script. Instead, you imagine a future where your project has failed and ask yourself:

Why did this happen?

At first, this might sound a bit gloomy, but it’s not about being pessimistic. It’s actually a super practical way of spotting potential pitfalls before they become problems.

Psychologists call this prospective hindsight.

A study in the journal Psychological Science found that imagining a failure ahead of time makes us way better at identifying risks compared to just brainstorming things that might go wrong.

By putting ourself in the mindset of a future failure, we unlock a different way of thinking. It helps us tap into this mode of deeper creativity and critical problem-solving.

The Power of Negative Visualisation

This idea of thinking through worst-case scenarios isn’t new though.

The ancient Stoics, like Seneca and Marcus Aurelius, called it premeditatio malorum — literally, “the premeditation of evils.”

They’d actively imagine the worst that could happen — not because they enjoyed freaking themselves out, but because it prepared them for anything life threw their way. And as a bonus, it helped them appreciate the good stuff in the present.

Modern psychology backs this up, too.

Research on something called counterfactual thinking — basically imagining alternative outcomes — shows that reflecting on negative possibilities can actually boost resilience and motivation.

When we think through what could go wrong, we feel more prepared to tackle challenges.

Why Premortems Boost Success

What’s brilliant about the premortem technique is how it cuts through common mental traps like overconfidence and groupthink.

Daniel Kahneman and Amos Tversky — the psychologists behind Thinking, Fast and Slow — talk about something called the planning fallacy. It’s our natural tendency to underestimate how much time, effort, and resources we’ll actually need to complete a goal.

The premortem technique, then, is like a mental reality check: it forces us to confront uncomfortable truths and think more critically about our plans.

For example, during NASA’s planning for the Mars Rover missions, they ran something similar to a premortem called “failure mode analysis.” They imagined all the ways the mission could fail — and then worked backward to prevent those failures.

So it was partly this way of thinking that led to the mission’s eventual success.

Obviously, most of us aren’t launching Mars Rovers. But the premortem works just as well for everyday projects.

Say you’re starting a business. Instead of just daydreaming about how great it’s going to be, you take a moment to imagine it failing. Maybe you run out of cash, your product doesn’t land, or a competitor beats you to the punch.

By thinking through those scenarios now, you can prepare for them or even avoid them entirely. Plus, this process often sparks creative solutions you might never have considered otherwise.

The premortem technique isn’t just about avoiding failure. It’s about building resilience and unlocking innovation.

By proactively anticipating challenges, we set ourselves up to adapt and thrive no matter what happens.

Maximising Your Chances of Success

Of course, staying prepared isn’t something you just do once. It’s a skill that needs regular practice and sharpening.

That’s exactly where Productivity Lab (https://djX7c204.eu1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/5H+113/djX7c204/VVKLkk751HhcW8FLr2Y46hT2zW63xJzN5nR2gYN3cFw5-3pyd0W7lCdLW6lZ3lKW7JhB0H7tK_2jW6NdyRj6w_gCHW32vHrQ8pNRcWW7zWbv07kck7tW7VRj7v8vbf-KVcM7rQ1jgrDlW4Lbc6f3td7KjW73y5Sf1JBDNJW2fZjCV8NM_PTW7pC4137Z9HSsW2klhcD4z63pfW5KzT5H3MtMyBW3YnjKg5jlT59W3T2cQ76PRx_7W24v8vp5hP-Z0W7pGMLP8Zwyl0W145Jfz2kFlW0W7b8mkv9kwcfJW53xrYg7CT20WVydfsM10jRwWW8Nvrs96Sx5BjW4DSrkw1ClrnGW2-pGTc1Z24YYW4V7PVf51FsZkf5FPTs804 )  comes in.

column7: 🚀 What's new in Replit: Sonnet 4, Security, & more
column9:
May was an a-may-zing month for updates at Replit: Sonnet 4.0, safe vibe 
coding, new integrations, visual edits & more!



 <https://replit.com>



Tuesday, June 3, 2025


May was an a-may-zing month for updates at Replit.

... Ok, I’ll show myself out. If this is the last email you get from me, that 
pun finally did me in.

But seriously, it was a big month. We shipped a ton of features you won’t want 
to miss. Check them out and let us know what you think.

May's updates include:


 * Sonnet 4.0 in Agent: We're shipping the latest and greatest models on day-1
 * Safe vibe coding: Security Scan, checkpoint improvements, Replit Auth
 * New integrations: Build with Notion, PayPal, and Google Analytics
 * Visual edits: Bringing you a new, improved editing experience

and much, much more!




🆕 Sonnet 4 in Agent



Replit Agent is now powered by Claude Sonnet 4.0.

 We partnered with Anthropic to bring you the latest & greatest Sonnet the 
same day as the release. You'll notice improved Agent performance and speed. ✌️


🔒Safe Vibe Coding


 <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o76diiNCJwA>

This month, we dialed in safety.

 We now prevent accidental pasting of API keys into Agent chat and warn about 
sensitive data. We've also introduced comprehensiveSecurity Scans 
<https://docs.replit.com/replit-workspace/workspace-features/security-scanner#security-scanner>
 for your entire Agent project to find and report potential vulnerabilities in 
realtime thanks to Semgrep.

 Last, but definitely not least, Auth 
<https://docs.replit.com/replit-workspace/replit-auth#replit-auth> is out for 
all users to quickly add log-in to your apps, securely. Check out the launch 
video above for all the deets 🔐


🤝 Notion + Replit


 <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AOYqTONf07o>

Our new Notion integration is live! You can now build Apps with Replit that 
push or pull data from Notion.

That means you can build a completely customized blog with Notion pages as 
data or a workout tracker that outputs data to a Notion DB.

 You can dive-in with our interactive tutorial above. You can also follow 
along in our docshere 
<https://docs.replit.com/tutorials/build-a-notion-powered-website>.


🖌️ Visual Editor



We've revamped our visual editor.

 The Visual Editor lets you select elements in your app's preview and edit 
them directly. You can change text right from the preview, adjust styles like 
padding and colors with simple controls, and see all changes instantly.

When you're done, your code updates automatically, saving you time and effort. 
Learn more in ourdocs. 
<https://docs.replit.com/replitai/visual-editor#visual-editor> 


📌 Other new features


 * Enhanced Checkpoints & Time Travel: Agent checkpoints just got a whole lot 
better—you can now view an entire history of your checkpoints in Agent.Time 
Travel <https://x.com/_jzhao/status/1923095488527548622> means you can see a 
preview of your app at any point in time
 * PayPal & Google Analytics Agent integrations: Add PayPal checkout and GA to 
your Agent apps in seconds. Learn more about our Agent Integrationshere 
<https://docs.replit.com/replitai/integrations#paypal>
 * Enterprise and teams: Protected development previews for secure iteration, 
viewer seats for broader team collaboration, & advanced seat management (SCIM)
 * Performance improvements: Backend performance and reliability improvements, 
bringing faster Agent responses. 90% of Agent responses are now 90% faster
 * Extended preview times: Previews are now active for a default 10 minutes 
when navigating away from your apps—this is up from our previous 20 seconds
 * Auth gets even better: We've made Auth 
<https://docs.replit.com/replit-workspace/replit-auth#replit-auth> available to 
all users—add login to your apps in seconds ask Agent "add auth" or "add login"

 You can also find weekly updates in our Changelog! 
<https://docs.replit.com/updates>


📹 Videos & tutorials


 I've been shipping tutorials weekly on my channel 
<https://www.youtube.com/@mattpalmer> and the Replit YouTube 
<https://www.youtube.com/@replit>. Here are some highlights from this month:




 <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2v5Fs7Xr11Y>

End-to-end vibe coding: Follow along for an end-to-end tutorial on building 
and deploying a map of parks in San Francisco. Follow along in our docshere. 
<https://docs.replit.com/tutorials/vibe-coding-101>


 <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FepR-sBZKCo>

column7: Apache Iceberg Isn't Coming To Save You
column9:
View this post on the web at https://seattledataguy.substack.com/p/apache-iceberg-isnt-coming-to-save

Hi, fellow future and current Data Leaders; Ben here 👋
Today I wanted to talk about Iceberg. I’ve been seeing a lot about it recently. Everyone wants to be involved in the open table format business. But my question is, will it actually solve a business problem? 
Before we dive into the article, I’m also excited to share that I'm putting together recordings of my 6-week Data Leaders Playbook Accelerator, which I'll be running again in September. This six-week program is designed to help data leaders drive greater impact and play a more strategic role within their company. If you’re interested, you can sign up for the program here. [ https://substack.com/redirect/a926a010-0313-4d34-93b6-218d284684a4?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]
With that let’s jump into the article!
Intro
Maybe I’m biased. I love new tools. Like many technophiles, I’m drawn to new solutions. Yet, I still feel I need to pause and question when a new tool is posed as the savior of the data world.
Many people are searching for a silver bullet and assume it must be a new piece of technology. And vendors love it—they lean in. They coin new terms, repackage old ones, and flood the space with “best practices” and design patterns built to hook our curiosity.
And let’s be honest: part of what drew many of us to tech in the first place was the appeal of solving complex problems. Nothing scratches that itch like a new tool packed with just enough nuance and edge cases to unravel.
But lately, I’ve been asking myself a different question—especially when it comes to technologies like Apache Iceberg:
Do we even know what problem we’re trying to solve?
What Question Does Iceberg Solve?
When people start rattling off reasons why Iceberg is great, I can’t help but think of something Shachar [ https://substack.com/redirect/94960434-f96d-412b-8c5a-70b534012a38?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] posted:
What in the world is the question you’re trying to answer?
You’ll often hear folks say Iceberg is vendor-agnostic, or that it supports time travel. Fair enough, time travel can be useful, especially in terms of data management( I will talk about my thoughts on it being vendor agnostic later). One example I’ve heard is that it helps you avoid creating four versions of the same table while testing. Helpful, sure. But it’s not exactly a killer reason to switch.
Truthfully, I haven’t yet seen a use case that makes you want to toss everything else out and go all-in on Iceberg. (And I’m sure I’ll get a few comments or DMs after this article).
To be clear, I’m not saying larger companies can’t benefit. If you’ve got an experienced team and a mature platform, you might be able to take advantage of what Iceberg offers. But if you’re a small team, or just not a Big Tech company, I don’t think you’ll get the payoff you expect.
I’ve found myself quoting this article a lot lately, but it still resonates even though it was written over two decades ago:
Remember that the architecture people are solving problems that they think they can solve, not problems which are useful to solve. Soap + WSDL may be the Hot New Thing, but it doesn’t really let you do anything you couldn’t do before using other technologies —(who knew Joel had access to chatgpt so long ago) if you had a reason to - Joel Spolsky Don’t Let Architecture Astronauts Scare You [ https://substack.com/redirect/477b2503-5df5-43d2-a599-a9b4dc063255?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]
I think many of us cling to new tools because they let us focus on problems we know how to solve, things we can control, rather than focusing on messier, more ambiguous challenges of understanding the business.
Even if you read a dozen articles like the one above, understanding the business in practice is far harder. As Aaron Wilkerson  noted [ https://substack.com/redirect/69f23ffa-fdb2-4a91-81fb-14fb2321d393?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], some lessons you just have to live through. You can’t look up stakeholder buy-in on Stack Overflow because each one might need a different approach, and that approach can change depending on the day.
So instead, we retreat to what we can control, even if we’re solving problems the business won’t ultimately value.
SeattleDataGuy’s Newsletter is a reader-supported publication. To receive new posts and support my work, consider becoming a free or paid subscriber.
The Central Truth
One of the arguments suggesting that Iceberg could help improve your data strategy [ https://substack.com/redirect/3d56ddec-a80c-4e7e-a481-814b8bfdf5e9?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] is the fact that it’s vendor-agnostic. I actually just saw a post on LinkedIn that said something like, “We need to focus less on tech and more on the business,” and then went on and listed a dozen tools, including Iceberg, somehow suggesting that being vendor agnostic is what will create business value.
The irony.
I do agree that if used correctly, Iceberg could act like a more true centralized source of truth.
In the past, so many vendors and products pitched themselves as a single source of truth. Of course, they would end up siloing data into yet another database, whether that be Oracle or Teradata.
Even now, many companies I’ve worked with or spoken to have hybrid set-ups where Databricks might act as their ML workflow solution and Snowflake their data warehouse layer [ https://substack.com/redirect/64a3e748-92d3-4f69-8675-d6b5202fef22?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ](despite obviously both companies not wanting that to be the case) the data might exist in various forms in an S3 [ https://substack.com/redirect/4f0eb119-5814-45a4-8dcf-c1062cc4ff74?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] bucket and Snowflake and then you’re having to port it all around.
In that world, Iceberg won’t save your data strategy. It also won’t drive business impact. However, it will reduce the friction required to deploy data workflows. Instead of having to port data around, you could interact with data as you please with the data engine you wanted. That is one of the benefits that many toute when it comes to Icebergs, and it does make sense.
That is until you realize many of the issues many larger organizations face that would benefit from this are organizational, not technical.
Every VP wants to own their own fiefdom of projects, and everyone wants their own data workflows. So, somehow, most companies would likely end up with three different implementations of Iceberg [ https://substack.com/redirect/1c4b57f6-8391-4047-a0be-d6bea5430a9e?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] with six different catalogs. But hey, that problem could be an opportunity.
So We Shouldn’t Use Iceberg?
When I first got into data, Hadoop was at its peak. It felt inescapable—every conference featured Hortonworks and Cloudera.
Data Lakes  [ https://substack.com/redirect/44b912ca-b221-4c18-abed-be38228d1abe?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]were the future.
Now, a decade later, Hadoop's search trends have fallen off like a one-hit-wonder. But to say it didn’t help shape today’s data landscape would be shortsighted.
Many great projects, like Presto/Trino [ https://substack.com/redirect/73b68613-9854-4099-9ef9-0f7d78b2f37b?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] and the Hive Metastore  [ https://substack.com/redirect/458406b1-4d15-4038-8f77-d8404213dd74?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ], emerged from the Hadoop era. They were built to address the pain points people faced working with the original tech.
I’m not saying you shouldn’t learn Iceberg. But I’d be cautious about deploying it unless it solves a very specific problem you’re actually facing.
And if you’re spending $10K a year on Snowflake [ https://substack.com/redirect/183bef2e-6aad-4bba-98c6-742227073c0b?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]? I’d wager a migration probably isn’t worth it. Just a hunch.
I made a similar point in my Columnar storage [ https://substack.com/redirect/2bc76e8a-9d0b-4dd9-81b4-e0ef55a9a37d?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] article, where I mentioned how Uber saved money and storage by switching compression formats. But Uber operates at a massive scale, where those changes actually move the needle.
Do you?
Iceberg Is Not A Strategy
If your data team isn’t driving value or engaging with the business, switching to Iceberg, or dbt or Presto, for that matter, won’t magically fix your problems.
Writing SQL faster won’t save a broken data strategy. Swapping one tool for another won’t either.
Actually, I want you to pause. Close your eyes.
Let’s say you build your dream architecture. Iceberg is humming along at the center of it all. Now what?
How are you delivering value to the business? If all technical friction disappeared tomorrow, what would you actually do?
It’s like asking: if you suddenly had $100 million, how would you spend your free time? Most people don’t have a clear answer.
And if you don’t, maybe you’ll just chase the next shiny tool.
On the flip side, if your data team is already delivering value and you’re looking to improve workflows, Iceberg might be worth exploring. It could absolutely have a place in a more mature stack.
But that’s not the same as saying it is the strategy. Because tools don’t solve business problems, people do.
Final Thoughts
As technophiles, it’s hard to escape the FOMO.
Netflix is using a new technology, shouldn’t we be using it, too?
Our favorite tool just released a new design paradigm, better dive in and implement it immediately, right? Surely, it’s been battle-tested. But after the migration, you usually find there’s a trade-off. There always is.
Maybe you ditched Teradata for Hadoop and saved on licensing, only to spend that or more hiring more engineers to manage the complexity.
That’s why, as a data engineer or architect, it’s worth stepping back and asking the harder question: Does this tool actually benefit my company? Or am I just chasing infrastructure for infrastructure’s sake?
As always, thanks for reading.
Join My Data Engineering And Data Science Discord
If you’re looking to talk more about data engineering, data science, breaking into your first job, and finding other like minded data specialists. Then you should join the Seattle Data Guy discord!
We are now over 8000 members!
Join My Technical Consultants Community
If you’re a data consultant or considering becoming one then you should join the Technical Freelancer Community! We have over 1500 members!
You’ll find plenty of free resources you can access to expedite your journey as a technical consultant as well as be able to talk to other consultants about questions you may have!
Articles Worth Reading
There are thousands of new articles posted daily all over the web! I have spent a lot of time sifting through some of these articles as well as TechCrunch and companies tech blog and wanted to share some of my favorites!
Petabyte-scale data migration made simple: AppsFlyer’s best practice journey with Amazon EMR Serverless
Organizations worldwide aim to harness the power of data to drive smarter, more informed decision-making by embedding data at the core of their processes. Using data-driven insights enables you to respond more effectively to unexpected challenges, foster innovation, and deliver enhanced experiences to your customers. In fact, data has transformed how organizations drive decision-making, but historically, managing the infrastructure to support it posed significant challenges and required specific skill sets and dedicated personnel. The complexity of setting up, scaling, and maintaining large-scale data systems impacted agility and pace of innovation. This reliance on experts and intricate setups often diverted resources from innovation, slowed time-to-market, and hindered the ability to respond to changes in industry demands.
Read More Here [ https://substack.com/redirect/380ff147-aabc-473f-81c2-794b1294cbaa?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]
End Of Day 181
Thanks for checking out our community. We put out 4-5 Newsletters a month discussing data, tech, and start-ups.
If you enjoyed it, consider liking, sharing and helping this newsletter grow!

column7: How a beginner ghostwriter booked 19 sales calls
column9:
Hey there!

Are you falling into the trap of believing all freelance writers
are overworked and underpaid?

Can’t see how you’ll ever break the $4k, $5k, even $8k ceiling
your pushing up against without working 80 hour weeks?

Then, I’ve got some news for you:

You’re wrong—but it’s not your fault.

It’s easy to believe the writers have a hard time making ends
meet when all you see are freelance writers racing to the bottom
on Upwork or Fiverr.

But how do you beat these faulty beliefs? How do you see that
making a profitable living as a writer is possible and within
reach?

By surrounding yourself with a community of writers to inspire
you.

*****************************************************************
Making a lucrative living is a writer is easy—if you know how to
find and land high-paying clients.
*****************************************************************

Let’s take a recent win from a ghost from inside our Premium
Ghostwriting Academy (PGA).

Gama has been putting in the work inside PGA:

* He flew through the first modules, positioning himself as a
Premium Ghostwriter.
​
* He built his own Educational Email Course (an asset he could
use to showcase his service on any sales call).
​
* He crushed the outreach module, using the frameworks we teach
inside PGA to land 19 sales calls in just one week.

And the best part?

>From those sales calls, he now has the potential to close $54,000
worth of ghostwriting deals:

​
So, how do you fill your own pipeline with high-paying
ghostwriting deals?

*****************************************************************
3 dead-simple steps to fill your own pipeline with high-ticket
ghostwriting deals:
*****************************************************************

* Step 1: Create your Irresistible Offer. Every ghostwriter
should be clear on the specific person they help, the specific
problem they solve for them, and the specific (and unique) way
they do that for their clients. This is the 1:1:1 Framework and
it’s how you differentiate yourself from every other writer on
the internet.
​
* Step 2: Build your own asset. The best way to sell your
services? Prove it works for you. So, if you ghostwrite
newsletters, make sure you’re running your own newsletter. If you
do social ghostwriting, make sure you have an active social
account. This immediately builds trust with potential clients
when they come across your profile.
​
* Step 3: Do your value-first outreach. There are so many ways to
do outreach. The key is to use your Irresistible Offer as a frame
in all your messages to explain the problems your client has, how
to fix them, and the Ultimate Dream Outcome they get by fixing
these problems. This makes sales 100x easier.

Easy, right?

*****************************************************************
In our Premium Ghostwriting Academy (PGA), we help you take
action (and finally stop doubting yourself).
*****************************************************************

Inside PGA, we help you:

* Reposition yourself as a Premium Ghostwriter (so you can stand
out from all the other writers on the internet).
​
* Write and build your own in-demand ghostwriting asset—an
Educational Email Course.
​
* Find and pitch clients in your industry (without ever feeling
“salesy”).
​
* Delight your clients so you can build a lucrative network of
clients (and upsell your existing clients).

With all the steps laid out in front of you, all you need to do
is execute (and keep executing!)

And we have bulletproof accountability with your own 1:1
dedicated Success Coach who’s there to help you every step of the
way.

**********************************************
Ready to finally monetize your writing skills?
**********************************************

​Click here to build your own pipeline of high-paying clients (so
you can finally quit your soul-sucking job). (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/e5uw7qqv2wc7hpdxmkkc8h824qo22cl/g3h548nnhwu38p5pmdu3/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucHJlbWl1bWdob3N0d3JpdGluZ2FjYWRlbXkuY29tL2tpY2tzdGFydGVyLWNhbGw_ZWw9TndfT2N0OCZoZT1haWNvYWNoaW5nMjAyNSU0MGdtYWlsLmNvbQ==
)​
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Hope to see you in there!

Cole

Co-Founder, Premium Ghostwriting Academy

PS… Ready to make bank as a Premium Ghostwriter?

Kelsey’s story might be an outlier, but she saw her friend
crushing it inside PGA and just had to join.

Turns out, she crushed inside PGA as well.

(The bottom line: If you're willing to do the work, you will
probably get results too :)

It’s closing day! 🎉

 

Today is the last day to join my next cohort of students…

 

And start your path to become a Jay Shetty Certified Coach.

 

Fully trained, certified and ready to change lives.

If your name isn’t already on the list - please complete this form ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-closing-today-170-3&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+170-3&utm_content_name=Closing+TODAY+-+enroll+now%21&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ) and book in your enrollment call BEFORE midnight tonight.

Complete this application form ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-closing-today-170-3&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+170-3&utm_content_name=Closing+TODAY+-+enroll+now%21&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )It doesn’t matter where you come from.

 

What experience you have (or don’t have).

 

OR what background you come from. 

 

You could be:

 

✅ An office worker from New York

 

✅ A nurse from London

 

✅ Or a CEO from Stockholm

 

As long as you’ve got a passion for helping and coaching others…

 

And you want to finish your Summer 2025 with a new path ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-closing-today-170-3&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+170-3&utm_content_name=Closing+TODAY+-+enroll+now%21&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ) in your career as a people-empowering certified coach.

 

Then my team and I are here to help you achieve that dream.

 

Just like we did for Charian earlier this year:

“Wow! What a life-changing transformation I’ve been going through since joining this community…

 

Thank you so much for providing me with the tools and knowledge for building my life coaching business.” 

 

- Charian Eccles

Now it’s your turn, Candace...

 

To take everything you’ve learned so far in life.

 

And use it as the foundation of something greater - becoming a coach who helps others.

 

As one of the “Jay Shetty Certified Coaches of 2025”.

 

But to do that you MUST book your enrollment interview call BEFORE midnight tonight.

 

And attend later this week.

Click Here To Book → ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-closing-today-170-3&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+170-3&utm_content_name=Closing+TODAY+-+enroll+now%21&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )countdownmail.com-Jay Shetty, Jay Shetty Certification School ( https://call.jayshettycoaching.com/?el=booking-email-closing-today-170-3&utm_campaign=booking-be&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+170-3&utm_content_name=Closing+TODAY+-+enroll+now%21&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

 We’re thrilled to share an exciting update: We've teamed up with NASCAR driver
Chad Finchum and MBM Motorsports to bring next-level EMF protection to the
racetrack! As part of our new partnership, Chad’s pit crew and support team will
be protected from the high EMF radiation levels generated during races, making
this the first time an EMF protection solution will be used in the NASCAR Cup
Series.

Why racing? NASCAR is a high-stakes, high-speed environment with intense EMF
exposure from powerful in-car electronics and communications equipment. Our
advanced EMF protection technology is designed to help shield the driver and
crew from these risks, bringing safety to those on the frontlines of racing.

Check out Chad Finchum in the #66 car today at NASCAR Cup Series Race at
Homestead-Miami. Stay tuned as we pave the way for EMF protection

you are. Get ready for some awesome stuff coming your way. We recognize the
importance of protecting the privacy of the personal information you provide to
us. Accordingly, we have developed our Privacy Policy for you to understand how
we collect, use, communicate, disclose the personal information you entrust to
us. Your use of our site is conditioned upon your agreement with this Policy and
our Terms of Use. Before using our Service, please read our Policy on our site
carefully as it contains important information on who we are and how and why we
collect, store, use, and share your personal information. This Policy also
explains your rights in relation to your personal information. This Policy is
written in the English language. We do not guarantee the accuracy of any
translated versions of this Policy. Any translations are for your convenience
only. To the extent that any translated versions of this Policy conflict with
the English language version, the English language version of this Policy shall
control. Categories of Personal Information and Purpose for Collection We
collect the following categories of personal information: (1) contact
information including your name, email address, and mailing address; (2)
authentication information, including the user name and password that you use to
register an account on the Service; (3) financial information for payment
processing purposes; (4) user content, including survey responses, comments,
reviews, questions, and suggestions; (5) personal characteristics including age
range, date of birth, gender, marital status, and nationality; (6) personal
preferences including product preferences, online preferences, and interests;
(7) online behavior information including online activity, preferences, and time
spent viewing features; and (8) IP address or mobile network information. The
personal information we collect is required to provide the Service and customer
support to you. If you do not provide the personal information we ask for, it
may delay or prevent us from providing the Service or support to you. The
Company retains personal data for so long as reasonably necessary. If you
inquire about a career at the Company through our website(s)' careers pages, you
will also be asked to provide your resume. We utilize a third-party provider to
host our job applications and assist with the application process. Such a
third-party provider may have its own terms of use and privacy policies, and we
encourage you to review those policies whenever you visit their website or
interact with their platform. The Company will use the personal data of job
applicants solely for employment evaluation purposes. Providing this information
is completely voluntary. We may now or in the future provide customer support
via chatbox or email that utilizes artificial intelligence and natural language
processing to understand customer questions and automate responses to them,
simulating human conversation. However, by using our website, you agree to waive
the more restrictive laws and agree to be governed by the laws of the Canada. If
you wish to view our official policies, please visit our website. If you have
provided personal, billing, or other voluntarily provided information, you may
access, review, and make changes to it via instructions found on the Website. To
manage your receipt of marketing and non-transactional communications, you may
unsubscribe by clicking the "unsubscribe" link located on the bottom of any
marketing email. Emails related to the purchase or delivery of orders are
provided automatically – Customers are not able to opt out of transactional
emails. We will try to accommodate any requests related to the management of
Personal Information in a timely manner. However, it is not always possible to
completely remove or modify information in our databases. If you have any
questions, simply email support@drsquatch.com or visit our website to view our
official policies. By accessing and using our website, you explicitly accept,
without limitation or qualification, the collection, use and transfer of the
personal information and non-personal information in the manner described in our
Privacy Policy. Please read this Policy on our website(s) carefully, as it
affects your rights and liabilities under the law. If you disagree with the way
we collect and process personal and non-personal information, please do not use
this website. This Policy applies to this website as well as all web pages
Company hosts. It regulates the processing of information relating to you and
grants both of us various rights with respect to your personal data. It also

column7: [August] Deep Agents, OpenSWE, 1.0 alphas, and global meetups
column9:
LangChain's latest product updates, upcoming events, and use cases

To close out the summer, we’ve got a few updates — from alpha releases for LangChain 1.0 and LangGraph 1.0, to global meetups in Amsterdam and London. We’ve also shipped revision queueing for agent deployment and Deep Agents for conducting deep research. So, just like Taylor Swift made it official last week, your agents are ready to go the distance with reliable, long-running workflows powered by LangChain products. 💍

What’s new for LangChain?

OSS (LangChain, LangGraph)

💻 OpenSWE: Async Coding Agent

Open SWE is an open-source, asynchronous coding agent that acts like a true teammate. Built on LangGraph, OpenSWE connects directly to your GitHub repo, plans and reviews its own work, and goes to fix bugs or implement features. It is cloud-hosted, extensible, and designed to make long-running coding agents reliable and collaborative.

Read the blog post (https://dxxRf404.na2.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/JB+113/dxxRf404/VVtgBD6HZjYXW5zZB3G8rN-2KW63xJzN5C0qJQN7vvr1d3lcq-W8wLKSR6lZ3kRW4hrnBc5RN4dLW6vqSlw4M6S3nW3MwDN492J_dVVGmC4M4qyq3bW2GPqjJ1nxjBlW2rg7-42QYDBDW4YXf426Z8KHZN2V7p8PpfnYkW2h3Vzd976jlqW4-v9V247jbQZW5k23882kDL1CW1XZL9F5cLRd3W4Bg5m-91WVdpVXNXhp6xTkjgW61D87f1RvhL_N5mklFn2kpdLW5QHqW031tPLhW803nt13VV1fcW8cGZQR5Wsl6NW7cKskh3_lcbrW44Q25n2MSTV-W70m40h4k40ClW7-WDch8zJXN2W9fHQRP6w5FV9W4H9Ppw24gJNFW5dg8js3WWz0VW53_8Ln58hqlyW3LSMym9cmbjSf1PF7Dz04 ) — and when you’re ready, try it out. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/gku5p5g9m7swuke5wwuqt5qqme99fm/58hvh7hmvexmw6a6/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnV6enNwcm91dC5jb20=
)

Podcasting is the perfect combination of both
digital and analog media. And this has a lot to do with when it
was invented.

Podcasting started in the early 2000s, long before social media,
algorithmic feeds, and “going viral.” It was the perfect time for
podcasting to be invented.

It allowed podcasting to be digitally native while retaining the
original idealism of the internet, a democratized media where
everybody had a voice and anybody could listen to what was
important to them.

Podcasters uploaded new episodes, and listeners’ computers used
RSS to download them automatically.

There weren’t big tech platforms between the creators and the
listeners. There weren’t algorithms that amplified drama. And
there wasn’t an app trying to “hack your attention,” so you
binged a few episodes instead of going to sleep.

Podcasting was just real people sharing whatever was important to
them.

When compared with TikTok, YouTube, and Twitter, podcasting can
almost look quaint or less sophisticated. Maybe that’s true? But
I’d also argue that it’s much more healthy, not just for podcast
creators but also for podcast listeners.

I’ve joked that podcasts are the one type of media that accepts
you have a life.

YouTube strives for full engagement 100% of the time, TikTok has
another video if you’re bored for even two seconds, and anything
written needs your entire focus.

On the other hand, podcasts fit into your life rather than
consuming it. People listen to podcasts while working out, during
their daily commute, or while cleaning up around the house.

It’s why 80% of people listen to most or all of the episodes they
start. And this gives podcaster creators a unique opportunity to
engage their audience with long-form content that forms a genuine
connection.

On the technical side, podcasting is one of the only mediums
where creators retain a direct connection to their audience.

Creators on YouTube, TikTok, and Facebook are dependent on the
platforms to reach their audience. If a platform changes its
algorithm or business models, creators have to change their
strategy or risk losing their audience.

But when these same tech giants jump into (and out of)
podcasting, it barely registers. Listeners just flip over to a
new listening app, and the latest episode of their favorite
podcast is ready for download.

Even after 20 years, podcasting has stayed close to its roots and
offers an incredible opportunity for new creators.

There are 4.3M podcasts worldwide, which sounds like a lot until
you realize there are 114M YouTube channels and 600M blogs. That
means there are over 26 YouTube channels and 139 blogs for every
podcast.

Podcasting really is a level playing field. You don’t need a
team, you don’t need VC funding, you don’t need a high-tech
recording studio, or a celebrity guest to start a podcast (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/gku5p5g9m7swuke5wwuqt5qqme99fm/x0hph6hwwo6v7ri5/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnV6enNwcm91dC5jb20vYmxvZy9ob3ctdG8tc3RhcnQtYS1wb2RjYXN0
).

All you need is a cheap mic and something to say.

Keep podcasting,

Alban Brooke
Head of Marketing, Buzzsprout (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/gku5p5g9m7swuke5wwuqt5qqme99fm/7qh7h8h2vpd2efz/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnV6enNwcm91dC5jb20vP3V0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jb252ZXJ0LWtpdA==
)

column7: How I made $20,000/mo as a writer
column9:
One of the saddest things about ghostwriting?

People think ghostwriters are:

* Broke
* Unhappy
* And burned out

They believe the tired cliché of “Nobody makes a living as a
writer!”

But here’s the thing:

There’s a grain of truth to this cliché… if you’re a writer that
charges per word or per hour.

But there’s another type of writer that doesn’t do this—and guess
who’s making all the cash?

​
I know this is true because I was one of those writers charging
per word or per hour and I struggled to make rent (and I even
thought about going back to my 9 to 5).

But then I started charging for ASSETS and OUTCOMES and
everything changed.

*****************************************************************
You can build a lucrative Premium Ghostwriting business with this
simple reframe.
*****************************************************************

It took me thousands of hours to figure out how to package and

column7: Thank you for purchasing Free YouTube Boot Camp
column9:
Welcome to Free Data Engineering Boot camp! Company Logo [https://content.techcreator.io/logo/2-logo.png]
 We are thrilled to have you join us on this exciting learning adventure! Start
your journey by exploring the resources at the Free Data Engineering Boot camp
[http://url3905.techcreator.io/ls/click?upn=u001.tQ3Vi1AijXIbWru7gwnPRTUOkEbx1jvG06EiuN978X2jaWNsQQi-2B8NBbjtukgdfEJB9D_Y1m51lFTvlL9HkDfpa4XbMBl2QIwhiMna4O7rUFo7PDVvLl143SL1hWQ7EbgFsFDOXm-2Bp9MqbYmh5LYCi5azG99oNA8tsFlyIuWljHeL5REdS5y97K2GB-2Fs8-2BxUcFQYob9M2ywEQntUXvpzfhJUDVVWiielA4Z8bWVC-2Fhz4EYXxdSnYyDN2v4Mj4jBgGa2bI1IokMpRATBTscb7QelZGoQ-3D-3D]
. For more information about how the Academy works, feel free to check out the 
Academy Handbook
[http://url3905.techcreator.io/ls/click?upn=u001.tQ3Vi1AijXIbWru7gwnPRfzZUYzYXrRM0U3Q0aZGEldV4aAajQlbw-2FEsg8yHS6hLEvtmWtylz-2FArGiZFFON-2BbyqRtl3hxnkJPfYopb5G8ItOagF4qvC-2FQ-2FjFz6NEvcFfR4L8KtZeqlo-2F3ycBM6WyYuu1O2mKvpPruW9my-2FSXShc-3DETnC_Y1m51lFTvlL9HkDfpa4XbMBl2QIwhiMna4O7rUFo7PDVvLl143SL1hWQ7EbgFsFDOXm-2Bp9MqbYmh5LYCi5azG583Nvl9cCYQrG2g3ortGUrLlIAhTT-2FHLrtG6J-2BTSSdIr-2F45lLdRd5AElZBIh1nnIbu0KuDE74rJVcvPPUtk-2Bfn-2BEAqaTEhz80elrZtUVzqWAOCt2Ub-2FRGGCf-2BGFhkq57w-3D-3D]
. 

To help you get started, please take a moment to go through the information
below and address any relevant to-dos at your earliest convenience: 

 1. Join the Free Data Engineering Boot camp Discord community at 
    https://discord.gg/dQbZMTBj5q
    [http://url3905.techcreator.io/ls/click?upn=u001.tQ3Vi1AijXIbWru7gwnPRUv-2FPhAOt2sFsLwdmaM08ju0GjtkZ4iLF2-2BaShVNscSL8wiX_Y1m51lFTvlL9HkDfpa4XbMBl2QIwhiMna4O7rUFo7PDVvLl143SL1hWQ7EbgFsFDOXm-2Bp9MqbYmh5LYCi5azG9tSSkasAthXSy93Yg3fxNfKxlBxVo7CCNkfbVj6KvN1BVbY3xhONJCtAVnRitzn-2Bz3vy-2FqP4rNqwO4vwKvBt1aIYN-2FnhXC0eVBbn28MhgiEOORWS9KyD-2FDFFVrhU7NyLg-3D-3D]
    . This is where you can stay up-to-date about what is happening in the
    academy and connect with people in your cohort and across other cohorts. 
 2. Make sure that your Discord username in your academy profile
    [http://url3905.techcreator.io/ls/click?upn=u001.tQ3Vi1AijXIbWru7gwnPRTUOkEbx1jvG06EiuN978X0sfSwde4pXqqXyi2LOYhsiCQGKIYGKnAkIdzp0XgtMXQ-3D-3DMQoH_Y1m51lFTvlL9HkDfpa4XbMBl2QIwhiMna4O7rUFo7PDVvLl143SL1hWQ7EbgFsFDOXm-2Bp9MqbYmh5LYCi5azGzBUyVr-2BFGNQ0-2BITKA9vBiMkCAZ54YVGFDY4EnzJAAz0Kg7S4IRhvwaCJJmLDaUDdbHJOrKdyxHY86SastX9Pape3dwx5x1CivjzB6KP1gX6p4Ms0sJpyXiRKWUhsaDHyw-3D-3D]
    matches the one in the Free Data Engineering Boot camp Discord Community. If
    they don't match, kindly update it as soon as possible to avoid any
    potential permission issues.  * When updating the username, please do not
       provide a URL or any special characters like '@'. You might have the '#'
       sign followed by some numbers at the end, which is a part of the username
       and fine to include. 
    
    
 3. If you will be joining any of our live events on Zoom, please make sure to
    complete the following:  * Create a free Zoom account using the same email
       address you used to register for Free Data Engineering Boot camp. If you
       already have a Zoom account associated with that email, that's perfect,
       and there's nothing else you need to do. 
     * Log in to the Zoom account associated with your
       Free Data Engineering Boot camp email address before joining the Zoom
       meetings. 
    
    

To help you navigate our platform and get the most out of your learning
experience, please follow these steps:



 1. Check that we have the correct GitHub username in your academy profile
    [http://url3905.techcreator.io/ls/click?upn=u001.tQ3Vi1AijXIbWru7gwnPRTUOkEbx1jvG06EiuN978X0sfSwde4pXqqXyi2LOYhsiCQGKIYGKnAkIdzp0XgtMXQ-3D-3D-Iiq_Y1m51lFTvlL9HkDfpa4XbMBl2QIwhiMna4O7rUFo7PDVvLl143SL1hWQ7EbgFsFDOXm-2Bp9MqbYmh5LYCi5azG7Jv1tYK7kcAw3qD5fHCeDjsl4opOW2iLUzMt76z1HQMCJNVqbDRM4Uik7cqdd8gAzZppZAGgK0wbitn628phpe76jmASHuZSsYA8Y9z1BxjL3XKf93hpXS6Q543AiBIVQ-3D-3D]
    . This is crucial so we can invite you to our private 
    DataExpert-io-Community organization
    [http://url3905.techcreator.io/ls/click?upn=u001.tQ3Vi1AijXIbWru7gwnPRTfH9WmFC8DM9BzwhVmE9BwOa9w0RyRUlik-2FNtqcMY2CTjrrCu57-2FZBFCHglow870Q-3D-3DXFI3_Y1m51lFTvlL9HkDfpa4XbMBl2QIwhiMna4O7rUFo7PDVvLl143SL1hWQ7EbgFsFDOXm-2Bp9MqbYmh5LYCi5azG-2FfQSMMmuLq4ZYMSH7x0Qpz99xCwZc1vw8lxSNKvVvxN1MqyjZD-2FUYHdtvKgIc26Uj1MVwNRRBxUPVYf3CbrYvzSe06J-2BIxuN3zPIWDT0M3zMlXRp3T32K-2FbuMKH-2Fg1Xlg-3D-3D]
    , where you can access the code for the course and homework.  * To avoid
       issues inviting you to the GitHub organization, please check that the
       GitHub username in your profile
       [http://url3905.techcreator.io/ls/click?upn=u001.tQ3Vi1AijXIbWru7gwnPRTUOkEbx1jvG06EiuN978X0sfSwde4pXqqXyi2LOYhsiCQGKIYGKnAkIdzp0XgtMXQ-3D-3DhYA0_Y1m51lFTvlL9HkDfpa4XbMBl2QIwhiMna4O7rUFo7PDVvLl143SL1hWQ7EbgFsFDOXm-2Bp9MqbYmh5LYCi5azGxSviUDRMjO4SHxWvExr8-2BXgrh7O2FA89QpftHpt6deeumu-2BDibXVuy3T6XWHk6LORMrravzZc57KfaIexSJ3hxUYTohFgtu1LciMILS43-2Bf03ImN7mFjX1mmGXFqaGQcA-3D-3D]
       includes only the username. Please do not provide the URL or put the '@'
       symbol before it. 
     * Once we have
       the correct username, you should receive an email from GitHub informing
       you that the instructor "has invited you to join the @
       DataExpert-io-Community organization
       [http://url3905.techcreator.io/ls/click?upn=u001.tQ3Vi1AijXIbWru7gwnPRTfH9WmFC8DM9BzwhVmE9BwOa9w0RyRUlik-2FNtqcMY2CTjrrCu57-2FZBFCHglow870Q-3D-3DOoEc_Y1m51lFTvlL9HkDfpa4XbMBl2QIwhiMna4O7rUFo7PDVvLl143SL1hWQ7EbgFsFDOXm-2Bp9MqbYmh5LYCi5azG9P06zCoUwJtlf2hpqzJE-2FnVlj-2Fcuti3AgCSQsTBv4rP6w5c5-2ByejYrCUwk7f2fx8svLnIpYT3yY3SlT9bXz-2BNKKM9NxZbe1B9aIgaQLHeKLeOml7vbnCBpHdDuSfszRuA-3D-3D]
       ." Please be aware that you have just 7 days to accept the invite in that
       email before it expires. 
     * If you are
       having trouble receiving an invite, check your spam folder or go to the 
       DataExpert-io-Community organization

column7: From stuck to starting TWO non-profits
column9:
This week is the 5th Anniversary of the Jay Shetty Certification School. 🎉

 

And as I was reflecting on our journey so far, I was reading back through some of our 3,100+ students stories… 

 

This one really captures what we do here:

Your invitation to join my mission ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/5-years/?el=5th-bday-email-158-3&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+158-3&utm_content_name=From+stuck+to+starting+TWO+non-profits&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )
Neffeteria’s story is like so many others.

 

She was struggling to find her identity.

 

And had hit a roadblock in her career.

 

She knew her purpose was to help girls who struggled to connect with their parents…but she couldn’t seem to find her path to do that. 

 

Then…

 

Everything changed when she joined the Jay Shetty Certification School.

 

The skills and techniques she learned not only helped her become a professional coach.

 

But also create TWO non-profits to help girls.

 

AND she’s using what she’s learned to have deeper connections with her own daughters at home too.

 

This is exactly why we started this school 5 years ago.

 

If you feel like Neffeteria’s story resonates with you.

 

And you want to discover your own path and write your own coaching story in 2025.

 

Then click here and read this special invitation letter. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/5-years/?el=5th-bday-email-158-3&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+158-3&utm_content_name=From+stuck+to+starting+TWO+non-profits&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

-Jay Shetty, Jay Shetty Certification School ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/5-years/?el=5th-bday-email-158-3&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+158-3&utm_content_name=From+stuck+to+starting+TWO+non-profits&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

The Economist ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=e09df5c2ba13a8e01dbdf8a6957bd5cb7e2b4f58dd996a470d785ff806032f16380bf3c2970219d822af0a18f5e505a1ee1957ca1dfd460d94aa49e6d7f55a9e https://view.e.economist.com/?qs=32cbbf8aeb7b13fb6466a3718559c729cbdc5700da3a290180f74f19142636f4bda4923248eb648b324a8aabde724ef9fc7c8f56566b0eb77e362d4e308d8e11d326b88923e697a188efbf0188b745a6 Read in browser November 1st 2025 The Economist this weekend A special edition on passports and travel https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=e09df5c2ba13a8e0c98ecf1a6e876f5de376310fb4f62ceb90c4a607b09603b395307b3f66c1cc7b37945c87ebeea940c485cb4040df751b4e83c70664db0d03 https://click.e.economist.com/?qs=e09df5c2ba13a8e0e71aaf764e7ce775461d9cfa4b6e22135bf3d3925b683e0636a167b1978fa7dd9fc5fc156a79b31569cee4c68b725aa6 Michelle Hennessy Graphic detail editor Honeymoons are not usually a time for competition. But when one spouse has a more powerful passport than the other, it can be tempting. For ours, my husband and I went to the Uyuni salt flat in Bolivia. At immigration I handed over my British passport, had it stamped and walked through. He, travelling on his American passport, had to submit bank statements and provide our full itinerary, sit for an interview and pay cash for a ten-year visa on arrival. This was a demonstration of relative passport power: how far one can take you without a visa. Many Americans may have noticed that theirs now opens fewer borders than it once did. column7: Every ghostwriter should use this pricing strategy
column9:
This should be every ghostwriter’s pricing strategy:

Avoid the Middle.

Either be very expensive or be very cheap.

Most ghostwriters, when they sit down to come up with how much
they should charge for their service, they either:

* Close their eyes, wait for a random number to pop into their
head, and then decide, “That’s how much I should charge!”
​
* Or they look around at all the other people who provide their
ghostwriting service and then they go, “I should probably just do
that but maybe at a discount so I can compete on price.”

Both are really, really bad ways to think about pricing.

I can pretty much guarantee what you’re charging right now is
nowhere near the ceiling of what you could charge.

There are two reasons for why this is:

* You have a business model problem. You’ve picked the wrong way
to think about charging for the “value of your value.”
​
* You have some faulty belief about your own self-worth. You
think you’re not worth the price or there’s no way someone would
be willing to pay this. Or, because you’ve never seen someone
else around you charge his, so there’s no way you could do it
either.

But if you can solve these two problems, it will have a huge
impact on your earning potential as a ghostwriter.

So, let’s fix these problems, shall we?

)​

*************************************
Ghostwriters: Stop charging per hour.
*************************************

If you are charging per hour, stop immediately.

Nicolas Cole 🚢-->

@Nicolascole77

1. Charging per word
2. Charging per hour
3. Charging per month
4. Charging per asset
5. Charging per outcome

Accelerate to Level 4 as quickly as possible, then stay there and
stack cash. (

)
​
Charging per hour is a terrible business model because you are
tying your earning potential to time and effort. You can only
make more money when you work more hours, and you will never be
rewarded for creating efficiencies in your service or process.
Because if you get the work done in half the time, you make half
as much money—which is a huge problem.

And then on top of that, whenever you anchor yourself to per
hour, the client associates this rate with the hourly rate of
every other person in their life:

* Their lawyer
* Their dentist
* Their gardener
* Etc.

So you’re placing yourself in the context of every other vendor
that charges per hour, and most other people who charge per hour
are typically not charging a premium.

Even lawyers are way underneath the market of what they could
make.

But this isn’t your fault. Everyone price-anchors to hours. But
you don’t have to make the same mistake. Even if you were to
notch your hourly rate up to $500 or $1,000, you would still be
leaving a ton of money on the table.

Instead, charge by project and outcome.

***************************************************
Premium Ghostwriters charge by project and outcome.
***************************************************

The customer doesn’t care about the number of hours you work.

What they care about is the outcomes you deliver. They only care
about the number of hours you work because that’s the way you
told them you work. But if you were to charge by outcome (so by
project) instead, you can easily charge more.

Nicolas Cole 🚢-->

@Nicolascole77

Freelance writers charge per word or per hour.

Premium Ghostwriters charge per project or outcome.

Want to guess which one makes you more $$$? (

)
​
But to charge by project, you have to understand this fundamental
reframe:

You’re charging for your pattern recognition and experience, not
the hours you work.

*****************************************************************
Charge for the value you provide, not the hours it takes to
provide the value.
*****************************************************************

What the client is paying you for are all the years it took you
to acquire knowledge in order to deliver the outcome.

So, let’s say a client asks you to put together a document
outlining how to write the perfect marketing email. As a
ghostwriter, you might think that’ll take you 4-5 hours and you’d
charge $500 for it. But they aren’t buying your time. They are
paying for your pattern recognition.

If you think that the best way to be compensated on this is how
long it takes for you to create just the document or the
template, you’re leaving 10 years of value on the table because
that’s how long it took you to be able to create this in the
first place.

As a writer, you have to understand the value of your value.
------------------------------------------------------------

The client can take this document and easily get 10x, 20x, even
50x ROI on your knowledge if they were to teach it to their team
(or if you were to teach it to their team).

You’re passing along 10 years of knowledge to someone else’s
organization which they can use to get tremendous upside. So, why
wouldn’t you charge something like $50,000 for this? After all,
if they can use this to 10x their sales via email, then why
wouldn’t they pay that? It’s a steal!

Look at it another way. It sounds like a lot for a “project” but
really $50,000 is the equivalent of a fairly
entry-level/mid-level employee.

******************************************
Pricing boils down to your own self-worth.
******************************************

Did your mouth fall open when I dropped the $50,000 price tag?

If it did, then you don’t really believe you’re worth charging
that amount.

Nicolas Cole 🚢-->

@Nicolascole77

3 faulty beliefs that hold freelance writers back from raising
their rates ($$$):

• "I'm afraid the client is going to say 'No.'"
• "I'm afraid the client is going to get upset.
• "I'm afraid I'm not worth what I'm asking for."

All self-inflicted.

All wrong. (

)
​
You’re terrified and cannot fathom charging more than a baseline
hourly rate the “world” has told you is fair.

And I promise you, when you start to understand how higher-level
decision-makers make pricing & packaging and buying decisions,
they have no problem spending significantly more than you think
because they’re playing a different game, and they are not
concerned with the time or energy or effort.

They’re concerned about the outcome the service delivers—and you
can charge accordingly because what you know is WORTH that price.

Alright, now, onto some tactical advice.

*****************************************
3 more tactical ghostwriting pricing tips
*****************************************

* Tip #1: Avoid the Middle (or, in other other words, making it
less expensive won’t make people buy). The number that you pick
says a tremendous amount about your business. Let’s say I have a
Ferrari for sale. Everyone knows a Ferrari costs $300k-$500k. But
if I said I have one for sale for $500, you wouldn’t think, “Wow,
what a steal!” Your first thought would be, “What’s wrong with
the Ferrari?!” A huge part of pricing is understanding how the
price affects the customer or client’s perception of what you do.
Whenever you make something less expensive, fewer people buy
because they assume you aren’t the best. And why would they
settle for less than the best?
​
* Tip #2: The true ceiling of your current service is 2x, 3x, 5x,
10x your current price. I’ve lived this. When I was building my
ghostwriting agency, for the entire first year, we charged $2,000
or $3,000 a month for 3 articles/week. That was 12
articles/month. It was a tremendous amount of volume. It was
horrible. But after 2 years, we’d switched to charging $5,000 for
2 articles/month. The best part? Clients were actually happy that
we were doing less volume (because they couldn’t keep up). So
when you think, “No one would be willing to pay that,” know this
is just a faulty belief you have in yourself.
​
* Tip #3:Ask, “What would I need to do to charge this much?”
Don’t think “I can’t charge this much.” Instead, ask what you’d
need to deliver to charge the amount you want. This is a
packaging technique. Make a list of everything the client would
want. What would make them ecstatic for you to tell them or give
them? Then the price point rationalizes itself.

So, to wrap up, whatever you’re charging right now, I can
guarantee is nowhere near the ceiling of what you could charge.

Use these frameworks and tips to go out and charge more—and get
paid what you’re worth as a writer.

That’s it!

—Cole

Co-Founder, Premium Ghostwriting Academy

Hey Candace!

Tell me if this sounds familiar:

One day, you’re all in on ghostwriting, committed to making it
the side hustle you’ll use to escape your current job.

Then, the next day, you think graphic design might be the path
for you.

So you sit down and watch 4 hours of YouTube videos on how to
make your first $1,000 as a graphic designer.

And before you know it, you’re swirling with indecision:

*****************************************************************
“What happens if this is the wrong path? What if there’s a better
option?”
*****************************************************************

So you continue to explore different options (like copywriting,
dropshipping, crypto), thinking after a certain number of:

* $99 courses
* YouTube Videos
* And viral X threads

You’ll find the “right” answer for you, a path you can take where
you won’t fail and embarrass yourself in front of everyone who
said you would.

But here’s the brutal truth:

*****************************************************************
There is no wrong choice. The only wrong choice is making no
choice at all.
*****************************************************************

Because, all this “preparing” is a waste because you aren’t
moving in any direction. You feel like you’re in motion, but you
just stuck in one place.

You’ve committed to the safe path of “learning,” which is taking
you nowhere.

​

Because, if you commit you’ll finally have a path to follow—and
you can finally make 2025 the year you make change happen.

# **_10 Helpful Tools You Don’t Know Exist_**

1. **Julius AI**

  1. Description: A personal data assistant that makes data science accessible to all.

2. Category: AI Data Analysis

3. Do they provide a free trial: Yes

4. Website: [julius.ai](https://julius.ai)

5. Core features: Natural language data analysis, advanced visualization, regression modeling

6. ROI: Simplifies complex data tasks, saving time and resources for data-driven decision-making 

7. Tutorials: [Link](https://www.youtube.com/@Julius-AI/) 


2. **Taskade** 

  1. Description: Build your ultimate AI Agent workforce. 

2. Category: Workspace productivity

3. Do they provide a free trial: Yes

4. Website: [https://www.taskade.com/](https://www.taskade.com/) 

5. Core features: AI agents, AI automations, project views, integrations, Taskade AI, and more.

6. ROI: Significant time and cost savings for businesses 

7. Tutorials: [Link](https://www.youtube.com/@Taskade/) 


3. **BuzzClip**

  1. Description: Post daily user AI-generated TikToks in one click. 

2. Category: Social media marketing 

3. Do they provide a free trial: No 

4. Website: [https://www.buzzclip.io/](https://www.buzzclip.io/) 

5. Core features: AI UGC characters, multi-language support, viral hook creation, and direct publishing 

6. ROI: Time saved on social media marketing 

7. Tutorial: Available on their website in a 3-step format


4. **Inboundr **

  1. Description: Helps companies and their employees to create authentic LinkedIn content that drives brand awareness and inbound leads. 

2. Category: Social media marketing and lead generation 

3. Do you get a free trial: No 

4. Website: [https://www.inboundr.ai/](https://www.inboundr.ai/) 

5. Core features: Research assistant, entire team’s content creation help, conversations to content creation, trending topic suggestions, turn podcasts into content, and turn customer questions into content. 

6. ROI: Time saved on content creation and lead gen 

7. Tutorials: [Link](https://www.youtube.com/@Inboundr/) 


5. **ArchiGen**

  1. Description: It is the AI assistant for architects. 

2. Category: 3D Design 

3. Do you get a free trial: Yes 

4. Website: [https://www.archigen.online/](https://www.archigen.online/) 

5. Core features: Get interior and exterior renderings, realistic outputs, and 8+ design styles. 

6. ROI: Time saved in creating photorealistic renderings. 

7. Tutorial: Not available 


6. **Pollo AI **

  1. Description: Create AI images and AI videos using any AI model. 

2. Category: AI art generation 

3. Do you get a free trial: Yes 

4. Website: [pollo.ai](http://pollo.ai) 

5. Core features: Create videos from text, create videos from images, create videos with consistent characters, create animes from videos, create animations, and more. 

6. ROI: Time saved in creating image and video assets for marketing 

7. Tutorial:  [Link](https://youtu.be/XkoNNzBVjx4?si=tmvJGinpbzjrrUax) 


7. **Quizbot **

  1. Description: A cutting-edge artificial intelligence question generator designed with precision to revolutionize the process of question and exam development. 

2. Category: Learning 

3. Website: [https://quizbot.ai/](https://quizbot.ai/) 

4. Do you get a free trial: No 

5. Core features: Question generator, plagiarism checker, AI rewriter, AI content detector, multiple languages support 

6. ROI: Time saved in created quizzes for learning and lead generation 

7. Tutorial: Not available 


8. **Grok 3 **

  1. Description: An AI model prepared by Elon Musk’s xAI team. 

2. Category: LLMs 

3. Website: [https://x.ai/](https://x.ai/) 

4. Do you get a free trial: Yes 

5. Core features: Reasoning, coding assistance, live X and internet search, deep research, and better image generation. 

6. ROI: Time saved in brainstorming 

7. Tutorial: [Link](https://youtu.be/b0XI-cbel1U?si=dqPD3Wxyr0kaUVCo) 


9. **Studypotion AI** 

  1. Description: Turn lecture notes, videos, and articles into powerful study tools with AI. 

2. Category: Learning 

3. Website: [https://www.studypotion.ai/](https://www.studypotion.ai/) 

4. Do you get a free trial: Yes 

5. Core features: Generate study materials, chat with documents, and get instant AI notes. 

6. ROI: Time saved in learning 

7. Tutorial: Available on their website in video format 


10. **Motion **

  1. Description: Use AI to plan your work automatically. 

2. Category: Productivity 

3.  Website: [https://www.usemotion.com/](https://www.usemotion.com/) 

4. Do you get a free trial: Yes 

5. Core features: Calendar management, project manager, gantt chart manager, task manager, meeting assistant, and some more integrations. 

6. ROI: Time saved in workday planning 

7. Tutorial with review: [Link](https://youtu.be/99BzzE5P_YE?si=w7RnizQnhsivROiH)

We’re prepared to back it up, but we also know the value of social proof…

[https://funnelscripts.com/hosted/images/cd/eae5ff05d24336b9c0ac71e12b15ab/comment-2.png]

and neither of those options are great… especially when you don’t have a big
